67  *
68  * This code is quite usable. While more and more tests can
69  * be added (currently there is the initial test program, and
70  * another test program that is designed to stress-test every
71  * single function, and a third work-in-progress test suite),
72  * it does not change the fact that this code fundamentally
73  * works. Try out the `run_test_suite` script, and if
74  * everything works, it will tell you in green text that
75  * things work on your system. Any errors or warnings are not
76  * tolerated. This code should be usable for production.
77  * Configure to your needs. Generate your own with a custom
78  * prefix with the script at the top-level of the code.
79  * Philosophy of this is in the 'Articles' folder - and it is
80  * very unequivocal. -Gregory

233 /*
234  * benchmark_libc.c output
235  *
236  * memcpy 0.000010
237  *
238  * memcpy copy 0.000005
239  * __builtin_memcpy 0.000003
240  * Custom memcpy() (probably using __builtin_memcpy()) is 2.000000 times faster than default memcpy()
241  * __builtin_memcpy() is 3.333333 times faster than default memcpy()
242  *
243  * This means, theoretically, a 6-day operation could take less than 2 days. That's speed.
244  *
245  */
246 #ifndef FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY
247 #define FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY __builtin_memcpy
248 #endif

444 #ifdef __GNUC__
451 static inline size_t FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(size_t a, size_t b)
452 {
453  size_t result;
454 
455  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(__builtin_mul_overflow(a, b, &result)))
456  {
457  /* 0 on error (overflow). */
458  return 0;
459  }
460 
461  return result;
462 }
463 
466 static inline size_t FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul_ptr(size_t a, size_t b, size_t *ptr)
467 {
468  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(__builtin_mul_overflow(a, b, ptr)))
469  {
470  /* 0 on error (overflow). */
471  return 0;
472  }
473 
474  return 1;
475 }

493 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_CONST
494 static inline size_t FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_3(size_t a, size_t b, size_t c)
495 {
496  size_t result;
497 
498  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(__builtin_add_overflow(a, b, &result)) || FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(__builtin_add_overflow(result, c, &result)))
499  {
500  /* 0 on error (overflow). */
501  return 0;
502  }
503 
504  return result;
505 }
506 
508 static inline int FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_3_ptr(size_t a, size_t b, size_t c, size_t *out)
509 {
510  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(__builtin_add_overflow(a, b, out)) || FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(__builtin_add_overflow(*out, c, out)))
511  {
512  /* 0 on error (overflow). */
513  return 0;
514  }
515 
516  return 1;
517 }
518 
520 static inline int FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_2_ptr(size_t a, size_t b, size_t *out)
521 {
522  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(__builtin_add_overflow(a, b, out)))
523  {
524  /* 0 on error (overflow). */
525  return 0;
526  }
527 
528  return 1;
529 }

531 #else /* GNUC */
538 static inline size_t FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(size_t a, size_t b)
539 {
540  size_t result;
541 
542  if (b != 0 && a > SIZE_MAX / b)
543  {
544  /* Overflow */
545  return 0;
546  }
547 
548  result = a * b;
549  return result;
550 }
551 
554 static inline size_t FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul_ptr(size_t a, size_t b, size_t *ptr)
555 {
556  if (b != 0 && a > SIZE_MAX / b)
557  {
558  /* Overflow */
559  return 0;
560  }
561 
562  *ptr = a * b;
563  return 1;
564 }
565 
567 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_CONST
568 static inline size_t FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_2(size_t a, size_t b)
569 {
570  size_t result;
571 
572  if (a > SIZE_MAX - b || a + b > SIZE_MAX - c)
573  {
574  /* Overflow */
575  return 0;
576  }
577 
578  result = a + b;
579  return result;
580 }
581 
583 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_CONST
584 static inline size_t FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_3(size_t a, size_t b, size_t c)
585 {
586  size_t result;
587 
588  if (a > SIZE_MAX - b || b > SIZE_MAX - c)
589  {
590  /* Overflow */
591  return 0;
592  }
593 
594  result = a + b + c;
595  return result;
596 }
597 
600 static inline size_t FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_2_ptr(size_t a, size_t b, size_t *ptr)
601 {
602  if (a > SIZE_MAX - b)
603  {
604  /* Overflow */
605  return 0;
606  }
607 
608  *ptr = a + b;
609  return 1;
610 }
611 
614 static inline int FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_3_ptr(size_t a, size_t b, size_t c, size_t *ptr)
615 {
616  if (a > SIZE_MAX - b || b > SIZE_MAX - c)
617  {
618  /* Overflow */
619  return 0;
620  }
621 
622  *ptr = a + b + c;
623  return 1;
624 }

627 #define FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_increment(variable, label_if_fails) \
628  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_2_ptr((variable), 1, &(variable)) == 0)) \
629  goto label_if_fails;

631 // Adjust as needed. On embedded platforms or low memory systems, you might want to change the algorithm to be somewhat lower than 1.5x
632 // new len calculations need to be checked, before and after this, for overflow.
633 #ifndef FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_LOW_MEMORY_USAGE
634 #define FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_LOW_MEMORY_USAGE 12
635 #endif
636 
637 #ifndef FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ALLOCATOR_DIV_AMOUNT
638 #define FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ALLOCATOR_DIV_AMOUNT 2
639 #endif
640 
641 // Takes an argument and makes it at least 1 bigger.
642 #ifdef __GNUC__ // Check if GCC compiler is being used
643 
644 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_CONST
645 static inline size_t FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_REALLOC_REALLOCATION_ALGORITHM(size_t old_size_to_add_at_least_one_to)
646 {
647  size_t addition;
648 
649  // In 49 / 50 for example, Would equal 0. We need at least 1 of an increase.
650  // Default div_amount is 2 or in low memory mode 12.
651  // On embedded you could use low amounts.
652 
653  const size_t div_amount = old_size_to_add_at_least_one_to < FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ALLOCATOR_DIV_AMOUNT ? 1 /* divide by 1 and so double it. */
654  : FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ALLOCATOR_DIV_AMOUNT
655  /*
656  * not a really small number (under div amount),
657  * and so use the div amount
658  */
659  ;
660 
661  if (__builtin_add_overflow(old_size_to_add_at_least_one_to, old_size_to_add_at_least_one_to / div_amount, &addition))
662  {
663  /* 0 on error. */
664  return 0;
665  }
666 
667  return addition;
668 }
669 
670 #else /* GNUC */
671 // Fallback implementation for other compilers
672 
673 static inline size_t FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_REALLOC_REALLOCATION_ALGORITHM(size_t siz)
674 {
675  // In 49 / 50 for example, Would equal 0. We need at least 1 of an increase.
676  // Default div_amount is 2 or in low memory mode 12.
677  // On embedded you could use low amounts.
678 
679  const size_t div_amount = old_size_to_add_at_least_one_to < FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ALLOCATOR_DIV_AMOUNT ? 1 /* divide by 1 and so double it. */
680  : FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ALLOCATOR_DIV_AMOUNT
681  /*
682  * not a really small number (under div amount),
683  * and so use the div amount
684  */
685  ;
686 
687  // Check for potential overflow before performing the addition
688  if (siz > SIZE_MAX / 2 || siz > (SIZE_MAX - siz) / 2)
689  {
690  /* 0 on error (overflow). */
691  return 0;
692  }
693 
694  // Calculate the new size after 1.5x reallocation
695  const size_t addition = siz + (siz / div_amount);
696 
697  // Return the result of the addition
698  return addition;
699 }
700 
701 #endif

828 #ifndef FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC
829 /*
830  * One thing you can do, if you want "strict mode" on, you can define this to be and have -Werror on.
831  * That way, if any errors are not accounted for, instead of dealing with error handlers, the code just won't compile.
832  */
833 #define FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC static inline
834 #endif
835 
836 #ifndef FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_THREAD_FUNCTIONS_ENABLED
844 #define FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_THREAD_FUNCTIONS_ENABLED 1
845 #endif
846 
859 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_AGGRESSIVE_DIE_TYPE FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_aggressive_die = 1;
860 
868 #define FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_set_aggressive_die(mode) \
869  { \
870  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_aggressive_die = (mode); \
871  }
872 
879 #define FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_get_aggressive_die() FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_aggressive_die
880 
881 #ifndef FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled
890 #define FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled() \
891  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_aggressive_die)) \
892  { \
893  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FPRINTF(stderr, "Error: %s: %s.\n", __func__, strerror(errno)); \
894  exit(EXIT_FAILURE); /* Use default exit, only place in library this is used, adjust as needed. */ \
895  }
896 #endif

908 static inline void free_array(void **array, size_t len)
909 {
910  while (len--)
911  {
912  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(array[len]);
913  }
914  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(array);
915 }
916 
927 static inline void free_string_array(char **array, size_t len)
928 {
929  while (len--)
930  {
931  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(array[len]);
932  }
933  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(array);
934 }
935 
945 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *int_to_string(long long int number)
946 {
947  // Allocate a fixed-size buffer for the string
948  char buffer[FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_SIZE_STRING_OF_NUMBER_SIZE_PLUS_ZERO_TERMINATOR + 1 /* sign */];
949 
950  char *p;
951  long long a;
952  char *b;
953  char temp;
954  unsigned long long u;
955 
956  p = buffer;
957 
958  if (number < 0)
959  {
960  *p++ = '-';
961  number = 0 - number;
962  }
963  u = (long long)number;
964 
965  b = p;
966 
967  do
968  {
969  a = u % 10;
970  u /= 10;
971  *p++ = a + '0';
972  } while (u > 0);
973 
974  *p-- = '\0';
975  do
976  {
977  temp = *p;
978  *p = *b;
979  *b = temp;
980  --p;
981  ++b;
982  } while (b < p);
983 
984  // Duplicate the buffer using strdup
985  char *return_value = strdup(buffer);
986  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(return_value == NULL))
987  {
988  // Handle allocation failure
989  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
990  return NULL;
991  }
992 
993  return return_value;
994 }
995 
1005 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void int_to_string_with_buffer(long long int number, char *buffer)
1006 {
1007  char *p;
1008  unsigned long long a;
1009  char *b;
1010  char temp;
1011  unsigned long long u;
1012 
1013  p = buffer;
1014 
1015  if (number < 0)
1016  {
1017  *p++ = '-';
1018  number = 0 - number;
1019  }
1020  u = (unsigned long)number;
1021 
1022  b = p;
1023 
1024  do
1025  {
1026  a = u % 10;
1027  u /= 10;
1028  *p++ = a + '0';
1029  } while (u > 0);
1030 
1031  *p-- = '\0';
1032  do
1033  {
1034  temp = *p;
1035  *p = *b;
1036  *b = temp;
1037  --p;
1038  ++b;
1039  } while (b < p);
1040 }
1041 
1042 /*
1043  * @brief
1044  * This function is for maximally-efficient conversion of unsigned numbers to strings - no nonsense.
1045  * Output should be large enough to hold the number. length of "18446744073709551615" + null byte = 21 chars.
1046  *
1047  * @param unsigned_value The number
1048  * @param output The output buffer. Should be 21 bytes, or fewer if you are certain the number is small, of more if sizeof(size_t) > 8 (which is unlikely).
1049  */
1050 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void utoa(size_t unsigned_value, char *output)
1051 {
1052  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(output);
1053 
1054  char *p = output;
1055  size_t a;
1056  char *b = output;
1057  char temp;
1058 
1059  do
1060  {
1061  a = unsigned_value % 10;
1062  unsigned_value /= 10;
1063  *p++ = a + '0';
1064  } while (unsigned_value);
1065 
1066  *p-- = '\0';
1067 
1068  do
1069  {
1070  temp = *p;
1071  *p = *b;
1072  *b = temp;
1073  --p;
1074  ++b;
1075  } while (b < p);
1076 }
1077 
1087 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *uint_to_string(size_t number)
1088 {
1089  char buffer[FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_SIZE_STRING_OF_NUMBER_SIZE_PLUS_ZERO_TERMINATOR];
1090 
1091  utoa(number, buffer);
1092 
1093  char *return_value = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_STRDUP(buffer);
1094  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(return_value == NULL))
1095  {
1096  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
1097  return NULL;
1098  }
1099 
1100  return return_value;
1101 }

1113 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void print_uint_array(const unsigned long long *array, size_t size)
1114 {
1115  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array);
1116  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_PUTCHAR('[');
1117 
1118  for (size_t i = 0; i < size; ++i)
1119  {
1120  const unsigned int value = array[i];
1121  char buf[FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_SIZE_STRING_OF_NUMBER_SIZE_PLUS_ZERO_TERMINATOR];
1122 
1123  utoa(value, buf);
1124  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FPUTS(buf, stdout);
1125  if (i < size - 1)
1126  {
1127  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_PUTCHAR(',');
1128  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_PUTCHAR(' ');
1129  }
1130  }
1131  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_PUTCHAR(']');
1132 }

2543 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void *arraydup(const void *array, size_t num_mem, size_t size)
2544 {
2545  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array);
2546  const size_t tot_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(num_mem, size);
2547 
2548  // Check num_mem so safe_mul doesn't get confused.
2549  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(num_mem && tot_size == 0))
2550  {
2551  /* Handle memory allocation failure */
2552  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
2553  return NULL;
2554  }
2555  char *duplicate = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(tot_size);
2556 
2557  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(duplicate == NULL))
2558  {
2559  /* Handle memory allocation failure */
2560  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
2561  return NULL;
2562  }
2563 
2564  for (size_t i = 0; i < tot_size; ++i)
2565  {
2566  duplicate[i] = ((char *)array)[i];
2567  }
2568 
2569  return (void *)duplicate;
2570 }

3248 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *string_to_json(const char *input_string)
3249 {
3250  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(input_string);
3251  size_t escaped_length = 0;
3252  size_t input_length = 0;
3253 
3254  /* Calculate the length of the escaped string */
3255 
3256  while (input_string[input_length])
3257  {
3258  if (input_string[input_length] == '"' || input_string[input_length] == '\\')
3259  {
3260  // If the string uses most of memory and is filled with \ or ", there could be an overflow.
3261  // Check for this.
3262  // If you find this too slow, just change the macro definition.
3263  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_increment(escaped_length, overflow); // Need to escape with a backslash
3264  }
3265 
3266  // If the string uses most of memory and is filled with \ or ", there could be an overflow.
3267  // Check for this.
3268  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_increment(escaped_length, overflow);
3269 
3270  // Cannot overflow because it's a size_t that starts from 0.
3271  // (Actually, it can, if all of memory is nonzero.)
3272  // Do not check for this.
3273  ++input_length;
3274  }
3275 
3276  /* Calculate the length of the resulting JSON string */
3277 
3278  size_t json_length;
3279 
3280  json_length = escaped_length;
3281 
3282  // add 2 for double quotes
3283  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_2_ptr(json_length, 2, &json_length) == 0)
3284  goto overflow;
3285 
3286  size_t alloc_size;
3287 
3288  alloc_size = json_length + sizeof(""); // +1 for null terminator
3289  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(alloc_size == 0))
3290  goto overflow;
3291 
3292  char *json_result;
3293 
3294  json_result = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(alloc_size);
3295 
3296  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(json_result == NULL))
3297  {
3298  goto memory_error;
3299  }
3300 
3301  /* Add double quotes around the escaped string */
3302  json_result[0] = '"';
3303 
3304  // Start a 1 for j because index 0 is a quote mark.
3305  for (size_t j = 1, i = 0; i < input_length; ++i, ++j)
3306  {
3307  // Add unlikely because this isn't that probable.
3308  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(input_string[i] == '"' || input_string[i] == '\\'))
3309  {
3310  json_result[j] = '\\';
3311  ++j;
3312  }
3313 
3314  // i is the index for the input string and j is the index for the json result
3315  json_result[j] = input_string[i];
3316  }
3317 
3318  // Add the second quote
3319  json_result[json_length - 1] = '"';
3320 
3321  // Null-terminate the string
3322  json_result[json_length] = '\0';
3323 
3324  return json_result;
3325 
3326 overflow:
3327 memory_error:
3328  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
3329  return NULL;
3330 }
3331 
3344 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *strip(const char *str)
3345 {
3346  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(str);
3347  size_t end = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(str);
3348 
3349  size_t start;
3350 
3351  start = 0;
3352 
3353  /* Trim leading whitespace */
3354  while (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ISSPACE(str[start]))
3355  {
3356  ++start;
3357  }
3358 
3359  /* Trim trailing whitespace */
3360  while (end > start && FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ISSPACE(str[end - 1]))
3361  {
3362  --end;
3363  }
3364 
3365  /* Copy the stripped portion into a new string */
3366 
3367  // End is always greater than start. Should never underflow.
3368 
3369  const size_t memcpy_len = end - start;
3370  size_t alloc_len = memcpy_len;
3371 
3372  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(alloc_len == SIZE_MAX))
3373  goto overflow;
3374  ++alloc_len;
3375 
3376  char *result;
3377  result = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(alloc_len); /* Safe. */
3378 
3379  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result == NULL))
3380  goto memory_error;
3381 
3382  // Copy everything before the null byte.
3383  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY(result, str + start, memcpy_len); /* Safe. */
3384  result[memcpy_len] = '\0';
3385 
3386  return result;
3387 
3388 overflow:
3389 memory_error:
3390  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
3391  return NULL;
3392 }
3393 
3411 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char **split(const char *str, size_t *output_size, const char *delim, size_t max_times, int keep_delim_in_result)
3412 {
3413  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(str);
3414  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(output_size);
3415  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(delim);
3416 
3417  /* Count the number of tokens */
3418  *output_size = 1;
3419  const size_t delim_len = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(delim);
3420 
3421  for (const char *ptr = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRSTR(str, delim); ptr != NULL && (max_times == 0 || *output_size < max_times); ptr = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRSTR(ptr + delim_len, delim))
3422  {
3423  ++(*output_size);
3424  }
3425 
3426  const size_t new_len = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(*output_size, sizeof(char *));
3427 
3428  // Check output_size so safe_mul doesn't get confused.
3429  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_len == 0 && *output_size))
3430  goto overflow;
3431 
3432  /* Allocate memory for the array of strings */
3433  char **result;
3434 
3435  result = (char **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(new_len);
3436  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result == NULL))
3437  goto memory_error;
3438 
3439  const char *token_start;
3440 
3441  token_start = str;
3442  const char *ptr;
3443 
3444  /* Split the string into tokens */
3445  for (size_t i = 0; i < *output_size; ++i)
3446  {
3447  ptr = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRSTR(token_start, delim);
3448 
3449  if (ptr != NULL)
3450  {
3451  // Should not overflow.
3452  size_t token_length = (size_t)(ptr - token_start);
3453 
3454  if (keep_delim_in_result)
3455  {
3456  token_length += delim_len;
3457  }
3458 
3459  const size_t alloc_len = token_length + sizeof("");
3460 
3461  result[i] = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(alloc_len); /* Safe. */
3462  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result[i] == NULL))
3463  {
3464  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(result);
3465  goto memory_error;
3466  }
3467 
3468  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY(result[i], token_start, token_length); /* Safe. */
3469  result[i][token_length] = '\0';
3470 
3471  token_start = ptr + delim_len; // Move to the next token
3472  }
3473  else /* ptr is NULL */
3474  {
3475  // Last token, copy the remaining part of the string
3476  const size_t token_length = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(token_start);
3477 
3478  // The only way this could overflow is if strlen(token_length) == SIZE_MAX.
3479  //
3480  // But I don't see how that would be possible, because there would have to
3481  // be a null terminator for strlen() to work. So it would have to be
3482  // SIZE_MAX - 1, unless strlen() is broken. Since it would have to be
3483  // SIZE_MAX - 1, adding 1 to it wouldn't cause an overflow.
3484  // Therefore, this is safe code.
3485 
3486  const size_t alloc_len = token_length + sizeof("");
3487 
3488  result[i] = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(alloc_len); /* Safe. */
3489 
3490  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result[i] == NULL))
3491  {
3492  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(result);
3493  goto memory_error;
3494  }
3495 
3496  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY(result[i], token_start, token_length); /* Safe. */
3497  result[i][token_length] = '\0';
3498  }
3499  }
3500 
3501  return result;
3502 
3503 overflow:
3504 memory_error:
3505  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
3506  return NULL;
3507 }
3508 
3524 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *join(const char **array, size_t count, const char *delimiter)
3525 {
3526  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array);
3527  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(delimiter);
3528 
3529  const size_t new_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(sizeof(size_t), count);
3530  // Check count so safe_mul doesn't get confused.
3531  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_size == 0 && count))
3532  goto overflow;
3533  size_t *lens;
3534 
3535  lens = (size_t *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(new_size);
3536  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(lens == NULL))
3537  goto memory_error;
3538  size_t delimeter_length;
3539 
3540  delimeter_length = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(delimiter);
3541  /* Calculate the total length of the resulting string */
3542  size_t total_length;
3543 
3544  total_length = 1; // NUL byte
3545  for (size_t i = 0; i < count; ++i)
3546  {
3547  const size_t new_len = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(array[i]);
3548  lens[i] = new_len;
3549  total_length += new_len;
3550  if (i < count - 1)
3551  {
3552  total_length += delimeter_length;
3553  }
3554  }
3555 
3556  /* Allocate memory for the resulting string */
3557  char *result;
3558 
3559  result = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(total_length);
3560  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result == NULL))
3561  {
3562  goto memory_error;
3563  }
3564  size_t len_so_far;
3565 
3566  len_so_far = 0;
3567  size_t array_index;
3568 
3569  /* Concatenate strings with the delimiter */
3570  for (array_index = 0; array_index < count; ++array_index)
3571  {
3572  const size_t len = lens[array_index];
3573 
3574  /* Copy string */
3575  for (size_t x = 0; x < len; ++x)
3576  {
3577  result[len_so_far + x] = array[array_index][x];
3578  }
3579 
3580  len_so_far += len;
3581  if (array_index < count - 1)
3582  {
3583  /* Copy delimiter */
3584  for (size_t i = 0; i < delimeter_length; ++i)
3585  {
3586  result[len_so_far + i] = delimiter[i];
3587  }
3588  len_so_far += delimeter_length;
3589  }
3590  }
3591 
3592  result[len_so_far] = '\0';
3593 
3594  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(lens);
3595 
3596  return result;
3597 
3598 memory_error:
3599 overflow:
3600  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
3601  return NULL;
3602 }
3603 
3624 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int append_string_to_string(char **string, size_t *string_length, size_t *string_alloc_size, const char *string_to_get_appended, size_t string_to_get_appended_length)
3625 {
3626  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(string);
3627  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(string_length);
3628  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(string_alloc_size);
3629  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(string_to_get_appended);
3630 
3631  // Calculate the new length after appending the new string.
3632  size_t new_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_3(*string_length, string_to_get_appended_length, 1); // Adding 1 for null terminator.
3633 
3634  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_size == 0))
3635  goto overflow;
3636 
3637  // If the new length exceeds the current allocation size, reallocate memory.
3638  if (new_size > *string_alloc_size)
3639  {
3640  new_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_REALLOC_REALLOCATION_ALGORITHM(new_size);
3641 
3642  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_size == 0))
3643  goto overflow;
3644 
3645  char *new_string = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_REALLOC(*string, new_size);
3646 
3647  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_string == NULL))
3648  goto memory_error;
3649  *string = new_string;
3650  *string_alloc_size = new_size;
3651  }
3652 
3653  // Append the new string to the target string.
3654  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY(*string + *string_length, string_to_get_appended, string_to_get_appended_length); /* Safe. */
3655  *string_length = *string_length + string_to_get_appended_length;
3656 
3657  // Null-terminate the resulting string.
3658  (*string)[*string_length] = '\0';
3659 
3660  return 0;
3661 
3662 memory_error:
3663 overflow:
3664  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
3665  return -1;
3666 }
3667 
3668 #define FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_INITIAL_DATA_ARRAY_ALLOC_SIZE FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_INITIAL_STRING_ARRAY_ALLOC_SIZE
3669 
3692 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int append_data_to_array(void **array, size_t *array_size, size_t *array_current_alloc_size, void *data, size_t data_size)
3693 {
3694  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array);
3695  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array_size);
3696 
3697  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array_current_alloc_size);
3698  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(data);
3699 
3700  // The _no_alloc functions omit this for optimization.
3701  if (*array_current_alloc_size == 0)
3702  {
3703  *array = (void *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_INITIAL_DATA_ARRAY_ALLOC_SIZE);
3704  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(*array == NULL))
3705  {
3706  *array_size = 0;
3707  *array_current_alloc_size = 0;
3708  goto memory_error;
3709  }
3710  *array_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_INITIAL_STRING_ARRAY_ALLOC_COUNT;
3711  *array_current_alloc_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_INITIAL_STRING_ARRAY_ALLOC_SIZE;
3712  }
3713 
3714  size_t new_size;
3715 
3716  new_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_2(*array_size, 1);
3717 
3718  size_t mul;
3719 
3720  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_size == 0))
3721  goto overflow;
3722 
3723  mul = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(new_size, data_size);
3724 
3725  // Check new_size and data_size so safe_mul doesn't get confused.
3726  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(mul == 0 && new_size && data_size))
3727  goto overflow;
3728 
3729  // Realloc if needed.
3730  if (mul > *array_current_alloc_size)
3731  {
3732  const size_t new_size_total = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_REALLOC_REALLOCATION_ALGORITHM(mul);
3733 
3734  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_size_total == 0))
3735  goto overflow;
3736 
3737  void **new_array = (void **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_REALLOC(*array, new_size_total);
3738  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_array == NULL))
3739  goto memory_error;
3740 
3741  *array = new_array;
3742  *array_current_alloc_size = new_size_total;
3743  }
3744 
3745  /* Copy the data. */
3746 
3747  // Safe because *array_size * data_size is smaller than the number that
3748  // we checked for overflow.
3749  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY((char *)*array + (*array_size) * data_size, data, data_size); /* Safe. */
3750  ++*array_size;
3751  return 0;
3752 
3753 overflow:
3754 memory_error:
3755  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
3756  return -1;
3757 }
3758

3853 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int append_string_to_array(char ***array, size_t *array_size, size_t *array_current_alloc_size, const char *string)
3854 {
3855  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array);
3856  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array_size);
3857 
3858  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array_current_alloc_size);
3859  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(string);
3860 
3861  // The _no_alloc functions omit this for optimization.
3862  if (*array_current_alloc_size == 0)
3863  {
3864  *array = (char **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_INITIAL_STRING_ARRAY_ALLOC_SIZE);
3865  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(*array == NULL))
3866  {
3867  *array_size = 0;
3868  *array_current_alloc_size = 0;
3869  goto memory_error;
3870  }
3871  *array_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_INITIAL_STRING_ARRAY_ALLOC_COUNT;
3872  *array_current_alloc_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_INITIAL_STRING_ARRAY_ALLOC_SIZE;
3873  }
3874 
3875  size_t new_size;
3876 
3877  new_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_2(*array_size, 1); // Null terminator
3878 
3879  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_size == 0))
3880  goto overflow;
3881  size_t new_size_total;
3882 
3883  new_size_total = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(new_size, sizeof(char *));
3884 
3885  // Array size can be 0, which would confuse FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul.
3886  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_size_total == 0 && *array_size))
3887  goto overflow;
3888 
3889  if (new_size_total > *array_current_alloc_size)
3890  {
3891  new_size_total = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_REALLOC_REALLOCATION_ALGORITHM(new_size_total);
3892  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_size_total == 0))
3893  goto overflow;
3894 
3895  char **new_array = (char **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_REALLOC(*array, new_size_total);
3896  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_array == NULL))
3897  goto memory_error;
3898  *array = new_array;
3899  *array_current_alloc_size = new_size_total;
3900  }
3901 
3902  (*array)[*array_size] = (char *)string;
3903 
3904  ++*array_size;
3905  return 0;
3906 
3907 overflow:
3908 memory_error:
3909  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
3910  return -1;
3911 }

4005 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int prepend_string_to_array(char ***array, size_t *array_size, size_t *array_current_alloc_size, char *string)
4006 {
4007  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array);
4008  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array_size);
4009 
4010  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array_current_alloc_size);
4011  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(string);
4012  // The _no_alloc functions omit this for optimization.
4013  if (*array_current_alloc_size == 0)
4014  {
4015  *array = (char **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_INITIAL_STRING_ARRAY_ALLOC_SIZE);
4016  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(*array == NULL))
4017  {
4018  /* Die immediately if enabled */
4019  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
4020 
4021  *array_size = *array_current_alloc_size = 0;
4022  return -1;
4023  }
4024 
4025  *array_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_INITIAL_STRING_ARRAY_ALLOC_COUNT;
4026  *array_current_alloc_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_INITIAL_STRING_ARRAY_ALLOC_SIZE;
4027  }
4028 
4029  const size_t new_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_2(*array_size, 1);
4030 
4031  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_size == 0))
4032  goto overflow;
4033 
4034  if (new_size > *array_current_alloc_size)
4035  {
4036  const size_t new_size_total = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_REALLOC_REALLOCATION_ALGORITHM(new_size);
4037  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_size_total == 0))
4038  goto overflow;
4039 
4040  char **new_array = (char **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_REALLOC(*array, new_size_total);
4041  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_array == NULL))
4042  goto memory_error;
4043  *array = new_array;
4044 
4045  *array_current_alloc_size = new_size_total;
4046  }
4047 
4048  /* Move everything forward by 1 */
4049  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMMOVE(*array + 1 /* dest location */, *array /* src location */, ((*array_size++) * sizeof(char *)) /* size */);
4050 
4051  /* Set the string in the 0th position. */
4052  **array = string;
4053  return 0;
4054 
4055 overflow:
4056 memory_error:
4057  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
4058  return -1;
4059 }

4086 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int prepend_string_to_array_no_initial_alloc(char ***array, size_t *array_size, size_t *array_current_alloc_size, char *string)
4087 {
4088  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array);
4089  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array_size);
4090 
4091  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array_current_alloc_size);
4092  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(string);
4093  const size_t copy_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul((*array_size), sizeof(char *));
4094 
4095  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(copy_size == 0 && *array_size))
4096  goto overflow;
4097 
4098  size_t new_size;
4099 
4100  new_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_2(*array_size, 1);
4101 
4102  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_size == 0))
4103  goto overflow;
4104 
4105  if (new_size > *array_current_alloc_size)
4106  {
4107  const size_t new_size_total = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_REALLOC_REALLOCATION_ALGORITHM(new_size);
4108 
4109  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_size_total == 0))
4110  goto overflow;
4111 
4112  char **new_array = (char **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_REALLOC(*array, new_size_total);
4113 
4114  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_array == NULL))
4115  goto memory_error;
4116 
4117  *array = new_array;
4118  *array_current_alloc_size = new_size_total;
4119  }
4120 
4121  /* Move everything forward by 1 */
4122  /* Does not return an error. */
4123 
4124  // If array size plus 1 does not overflow, this should be safe.
4125  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMMOVE(*array + 1 /* dest location */, *array /* src location */, (copy_size) /* size */);
4126  ++array_size;
4127 
4128  // Set the string in the 0th position.
4129  **array = string;
4130  return 0;
4131 
4132 overflow:
4133 memory_error:
4134  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
4135  return -1;
4136 }

4154  {
4155  // NOTE: Do not check for overflows here.
4156  length += FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(array[i]);
4157  }
4158 
4159  return length;

4181 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *shellescape(const char *input)
4182 {
4183  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(input);
4184  const size_t input_len = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(input);
4185 
4186  const size_t size_with_null_t = input_len + 1;
4187  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(size_with_null_t == 0))
4188  goto overflow;
4189  size_t escaped_len;
4190 
4191  escaped_len = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(2, size_with_null_t);
4192 
4193  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(escaped_len == 0))
4194  goto overflow;
4195 
4196  char *escaped;
4197 
4198  escaped = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(escaped_len);
4199 
4200  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(escaped == NULL))
4201  goto memory_error;
4202 
4203  size_t j;
4204 
4205  j = 0;
4206 
4207  for (size_t i = 0; i < input_len; ++i)
4208  {
4209  // Escape special characters
4210  if (!isalpha(input[i]) && !isdigit(input[i]))
4211  {
4212  escaped[j++] = '\\';
4213  }
4214  escaped[j++] = input[i];
4215  }
4216 
4217  escaped[j] = '\0';
4218 
4219  return escaped;
4220 
4221 overflow:
4222 memory_error:
4223  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
4224  return NULL;
4225 }
4226 #endif

4240 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *reverse_string(const char *str)
4241 {
4242  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(str);
4243  char *new_str = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_STRDUP(str);
4244  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_str == NULL))
4245  {
4246  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
4247  return NULL;
4248  }
4249  size_t length = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(new_str);
4250  size_t i, j;
4251 
4252  for (i = 0, j = length - 1; i < j; ++i, j--)
4253  {
4254  char temp = new_str[i];
4255  new_str[i] = new_str[j];
4256  new_str[j] = temp;
4257  }
4258 
4259  return new_str;
4260 }

4290 static inline int ends_with(const char *str, const char *suffix)
4291 {
4292  const size_t str_len = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(str);
4293  const size_t suffix_len = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(suffix);
4294 
4295  if (suffix_len > str_len)
4296  {
4297  return 0; // Suffix is longer than the string
4298  }
4299 
4300  return strncmp(str + str_len - suffix_len, suffix, suffix_len) == 0;
4301 }

4311 /* @brief Cross platform memmem(). Slower though. We need to find a faster solution for Windows. Maybe using assembly. */
4312 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void *memory_locate(const void *haystack, size_t haystack_len, const void *needle, size_t needle_len)
4313 {
4314  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(haystack);
4315  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(needle_len);
4316  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(needle_len == 0))
4317  {
4318  return (void *)haystack;
4319  }
4320 
4321  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(haystack_len < needle_len))
4322  {
4323  return NULL;
4324  }
4325 
4326  const char *h = (const char *)haystack;
4327  const char *n = (const char *)needle;
4328 
4329  const size_t max_search = haystack_len - needle_len;
4330  for (size_t i = 0; i <= max_search; ++i)
4331  {
4332  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCMP(h + i, n, needle_len) == 0)
4333  {
4334  return (void *)(h + i);
4335  }
4336  }
4337 
4338  return NULL;
4339 }
4340 #endif

4356 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC size_t count_occurrences_of_substr(const char *str, const char *substring)

4361  const char *pos = str;
4362  size_t count = 0;
4363 
4364  while ((pos = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRSTR(pos, substring)) != NULL)
4365  {
4366  ++count;
4367  pos += substring_length;
4368  }
4369 
4370  return count;
4371 }

4465 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC size_t count_occurrences_of_substr_len(const char *string, size_t string_length, const char *substring, size_t substring_length)
4466 {

4628 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *longest_common_prefix(const char **strings, size_t count)
4629 {
4630  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(strings);
4631  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(count == 0))
4632  {
4633  char *ret = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_STRDUP(""); // Empty string for an empty array
4634  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(ret == NULL))
4635  {
4636  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
4637  return NULL;
4638  }
4639 
4640  return ret;
4641  }
4642 
4643  size_t max_common_len = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(strings[0]);
4644 
4645  /* Find the max common length among the strings */
4646  for (size_t i = 1; i < count; ++i)
4647  {
4648  size_t current_len = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(strings[i]);
4649  if (current_len < max_common_len)
4650  {
4651  max_common_len = current_len;
4652  }
4653  }
4654 
4655  /* Compare characters across the strings until a mismatch is found */
4656  for (size_t i = 0; i < max_common_len; ++i)
4657  {
4658  for (size_t j = 1; j < count; ++j)
4659  {
4660  if (strings[j][i] != strings[0][i])
4661  {
4662  /* Mismatch found, return the prefix up to this point */
4663 
4664  // Don't FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC 0.
4665  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(i == SIZE_MAX))
4666  {
4667  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
4668  return NULL;
4669  }
4670 
4671  char *result = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(i + sizeof("")); /* Safe. */
4672  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result == NULL))
4673  {
4674  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
4675  return NULL;
4676  }
4677  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY(result, strings[0], i);
4678  result[i] = '\0';
4679  return result;
4680  }
4681  }
4682  }
4683 
4684  /* All strings match up to the minimum length, return the entire prefix */
4685  char *dup = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_STRDUP(strings[0]);
4686  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(dup == NULL))
4687  {
4688  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
4689  return NULL;
4690  }
4691 
4692  return dup;
4693 }

4708 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *longest_common_suffix(const char **strings, size_t count)
4709 {
4710  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(strings);
4711 
4712  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(count == 0))
4713  {
4714  char *return_value = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_STRDUP(""); // Empty string for an empty array
4715  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(return_value == NULL))
4716  {
4717  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
4718  return NULL;
4719  }
4720  return return_value;
4721  }
4722 
4723  size_t max_common_len = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(strings[0]);
4724 
4725  /* Find the max common length among the strings */
4726  for (size_t i = 1; i < count; ++i)
4727  {
4728  size_t current_len = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(strings[i]);
4729  if (current_len < max_common_len)
4730  {
4731  max_common_len = current_len;
4732  }
4733  }
4734 
4735  /* Compare characters across the strings until a mismatch is found */
4736  for (size_t i = 0; i < max_common_len; ++i)
4737  {
4738  for (size_t j = 1; j < count; ++j)
4739  {
4740  size_t current_len = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(strings[j]);
4741  if (strings[j][current_len - i - 1] != strings[0][max_common_len - i - 1])
4742  {
4743  /* Mismatch found, return the suffix up to this point */
4744 
4745  // Don't FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC 0.
4746  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(i == SIZE_MAX))
4747  {
4748  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
4749  return NULL;
4750  }
4751 
4752  char *result = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(i + sizeof("")); /* Safe. */
4753  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result == NULL))
4754  {
4755  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
4756  return NULL;
4757  }
4758 
4759  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY(result, strings[0] + max_common_len - i, i); /* Safe. */
4760  result[i] = '\0';
4761  return result;
4762  }
4763  }
4764  }
4765 
4766  /* All strings match up to the minimum length, return the entire suffix */
4767  char *return_value = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_STRDUP(strings[0] + max_common_len); /* Should be Safe. */
4768  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(return_value == NULL))
4769  {
4770  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
4771  return NULL;
4772  }
4773 
4774  return return_value;
4775 }

4854 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void reverse_string_in_place(char *str)
4855 {
4856  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(str);
4857 
4858  const size_t len = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(str);
4859 
4860  /* Swap characters from both ends towards the center */
4861  for (size_t i = 0, j = len - 1; i < j; ++i, --j)
4862  {
4863  char temp = str[i];
4864  str[i] = str[j];
4865  str[j] = temp;
4866  }
4867 }

4878 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int is_string_valid_integer(const char *str)
4879 {
4880  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(str);
4881 
4882  if (*str == '\0')
4883  {
4884  return 0; // Empty string is not a valid integer
4885  }
4886 
4887  /* Check for optional sign */
4888  if (*str == '+' || *str == '-')
4889  {
4890  ++str;
4891  }
4892 
4893  /* Check for at least one digit */
4894  if (!FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ISDIGIT(*str))
4895  {
4896  return 0;
4897  }
4898 
4899  /* Check for remaining digits */
4900  while (*str != '\0')
4901  {
4902  if (!FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ISDIGIT(*str))
4903  {
4904  return 0;
4905  }
4906  ++str;
4907  }
4908 
4909  return 1; // Valid integer
4910 }

4921 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC size_t common_prefix_length(const char *str1, const char *str2)
4922 {
4923  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(str1);
4924  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(str2);
4925 
4926  const size_t len1 = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(str1);
4927  const size_t len2 = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(str2);
4928 
4929  const size_t min_len = (len1 < len2) ? len1 : len2;
4930 
4931  for (size_t i = 0; i < min_len; ++i)
4932  {
4933  if (str1[i] != str2[i])
4934  {
4935  return i; // Mismatch found, return current index
4936  }
4937  }
4938 
4939  return min_len; // No mismatch found, return the minimum length
4940 }

4951 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC size_t common_suffix_length(const char *str1, const char *str2)
4952 {
4953  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(str1);
4954  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(str2);
4955 
4956  const size_t len1 = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(str1);
4957  const size_t len2 = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(str2);
4958 
4959  const size_t min_len = (len1 < len2) ? len1 : len2;
4960 
4961  for (size_t i = 1; i <= min_len; ++i)
4962  {
4963  if (str1[len1 - i] != str2[len2 - i])
4964  {
4965  return i - 1; // Mismatch found, return previous index
4966  }
4967  }
4968 
4969  return min_len; // No mismatch found, return the minimum length
4970 }

4982 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *string_to_title_case(const char *str)
4983 {
4984  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(str);
4985 
4986  const size_t len = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(str);
4987  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(len == SIZE_MAX))
4988  {
4989  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
4990  return NULL;
4991  }
4992 
4993  char *title_case = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(len + sizeof("")); /* Safe. */
4994 
4995  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(title_case == NULL))
4996  {
4997  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
4998  return NULL;
4999  }
5000 
5001  int make_upper = 1; // Start with the first character as uppercase
5002 
5003  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
5004  {
5005  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ISSPACE(str[i]))
5006  {
5007  make_upper = 1; // Set the flag to capitalize the next character
5008  title_case[i] = str[i];
5009  }
5010  else
5011  {
5012  title_case[i] = make_upper ? toupper(str[i]) : tolower(str[i]);
5013  make_upper = 0; // Reset the flag
5014  }
5015  }
5016 
5017  title_case[len] = '\0';
5018 
5019  return title_case;
5020 }

5043  {
5044  if (array[i] > max)
5045  {
5046  max = array[i];
5047  }
5048  }
5049 
5050  return max;
5051 }

5185 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC size_t *generate_range(size_t start, size_t end, size_t step, size_t *range_size)
5186 {
5187  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(range_size);
5188  // Check for invalid range
5189  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(start > end || step == 0))
5190  {
5191  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
5192  return NULL;
5193  }
5194  const size_t size = (end - start) / step + 1;
5195 
5196  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(size == 0))
5197  { // Overflow
5198  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
5199  return NULL;
5200  }
5201 
5202  const size_t alloc_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(size, sizeof(size_t));
5203 
5204  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(alloc_size == 0))
5205  { // Overflow
5206  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
5207  return NULL;
5208  }
5209 
5210  size_t *range = (size_t *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(alloc_size);
5211 
5212  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(range == NULL))
5213  {
5214  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
5215  return NULL;
5216  }
5217 
5218  for (size_t i = 0, value = start; i < size; ++i, value += step)
5219  {
5220  range[i] = value;
5221  }
5222 
5223  *range_size = size;
5224  return range;
5225 }

6809  return (*(size_t *)a - *(size_t *)b);
6810 }

6953 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *read_file_into_string(const char *filename, size_t *size)
6954 {
6955  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(filename);
6956  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(size);
6957 
6958  *size = 0;
6959 
6960  FILE *file = fopen(filename, "rb");
6961  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(file == NULL))
6962  {
6963  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
6964  return NULL; // Indicate error by returning NULL
6965  }
6966 
6967  // Determine the file size by seeking
6968  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FSEEKO(file, 0, SEEK_END) != 0)
6969  {
6970  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FCLOSE(file); // No need to error check here because already going wrong.
6971  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
6972  return NULL;
6973  }
6974 
6975  // Get file size with tell
6976  const off_t file_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FTELLO(file); /* signed int type */
6977  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(file_size == -1))
6978  {
6979  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FCLOSE(file); // No need to error check here because already going wrong.
6980  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
6981  return NULL;
6982  }
6983 
6984  *size = (size_t)file_size;
6985 
6986  // Since off_t is signed, it should be less than SIZE_MAX, so don't check
6987  // if it equals SIZE_MAX before adding 1 more to it to FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC()
6988 
6989  // Seek to the beginning again
6990  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FSEEKO(file, 0, SEEK_SET) != 0)
6991  {
6992  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FCLOSE(file); // No need to error check here because already going wrong.
6993  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
6994  return NULL;
6995  }
6996 
6997  // Allocate memory for the file contents
6998  char *content = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(file_size + 1); /* Safe. */
6999  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(content == NULL))
7000  {
7001  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FCLOSE(file); // No need to error check here because already going wrong.
7002  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7003  return NULL;
7004  }
7005 
7006  // Read the file contents into the string
7007  size_t total_read = 0;
7008  const size_t file_size_size_t = (size_t)file_size;
7009 
7010  while (total_read < file_size_size_t)
7011  {
7012  const size_t read_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FREAD(content + total_read, 1, file_size - total_read, file);
7013 
7014  if (read_size == 0) // Not likely or unlikely.
7015  {
7016  const int error_code = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FERROR(file);
7017  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(error_code))
7018  {
7019  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(content);
7020  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FCLOSE(file); // Don't need to error check here because things are going
7021  // wrong.
7022  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7023  return NULL;
7024  }
7025  else
7026  {
7027  break;
7028  }
7029  }
7030  total_read += read_size;
7031  }
7032 
7033  // Null-terminate the string
7034  content[total_read] = '\0';
7035 
7036  // Close the file
7037  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(fclose(file) != 0)) // Check for errors.
7038  {
7039  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(content);
7040  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7041  return NULL;
7042  }
7043 
7044  return content;
7045 }
7046 
7061 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int write_to_file_with_mode(const char *filename, const char *content, size_t content_length, const char *mode)
7062 {
7063  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(filename);
7064  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(content);
7065  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(mode);
7066  FILE *file = fopen(filename, mode);
7067  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(file == NULL))
7068  {
7069  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7070  return -1;
7071  }
7072 
7073  /* Write the string to the file */
7074  size_t write_size;
7075  size_t total_written = 0;
7076 
7077  /* No need to check for EINTR. It would just slow things down here. */
7078  while ((write_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FWRITE(content + total_written, 1, content_length - total_written, file)) > 0)
7079  {
7080  total_written += write_size;
7081  }
7082 
7083  // Close the file
7084  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(fclose(file) != 0)) // Check for errors.
7085  {
7086  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7087  return -1;
7088  }
7089 
7090  return 0;
7091 }

7286 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int get_file_size(const char *filename, size_t *size)

7290 
7291  FILE *file = fopen(filename, "r");
7292  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(file == NULL))
7293  {
7294  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7295  return -1;
7296  }
7297 
7298  // Determine the file size with seek
7299  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FSEEKO(file, 0, SEEK_END) != 0))
7300  {

7302  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();

7308  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(file_size == -1))

7312  return -1;

7316  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(fclose(file) != 0)) // Error check
7317  {
7318  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7319  return -1;

7361 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int copy_file(const char *source_filename, const char *destination_filename)
7362 {
7363  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(source_filename);
7364  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(destination_filename);
7365  FILE *source_file = fopen(source_filename, "rb");
7366 
7367  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(source_file == NULL))
7368  {
7369  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7370  return -1;
7371  }
7372 
7373  FILE *destination_file = fopen(destination_filename, "wb");
7374  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(destination_file == NULL))
7375  {
7376  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FCLOSE(source_file); // No need to error check here because already going
7377  // wrong.
7378 
7379  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7380  return -1;
7381  }
7382 
7383  char buffer[FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_COPY_SIZE_AMOUNT];
7384 
7385  for (;;)
7386  {
7387  // Read from the file.
7388  size_t read_size;
7389  int error_code;
7390 
7391  /* Handle interrupted system calls */
7392 
7393  do
7394  {
7395  read_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FREAD(buffer, 1, sizeof(buffer), source_file);
7396  } while (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY((error_code = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FERROR(source_file)) && errno == EINTR)); /* Check for EINTR */
7397 
7398  // If it has finished reading or if an error has occured.
7399  if (read_size == 0) // Not likely or unlikely.
7400  {
7401  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(error_code))
7402  {
7403  /*
7404  * Here, we can distinuish between errors to ignore, and errors to to
7405  * about. Adjust this based on your environment or preferences.
7406  */
7407 
7408  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FCLOSE(destination_file); // Don't need to error check here because
7409  // things are going wrong.
7410  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FCLOSE(source_file); // Don't need to error check here because things
7411  // are going wrong.
7412 
7413  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7414  return -1;
7415  }
7416  else
7417  {
7418  break;
7419  }
7420  }
7421 
7422  /* Handle interrupted system calls */
7423 
7424  size_t write_size = 0;
7425  size_t new_write_size;
7426  do
7427  {
7428  new_write_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FWRITE(buffer + write_size, 1, read_size - write_size, destination_file);
7429  write_size += new_write_size;
7430  } while (write_size != read_size || FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(errno == EINTR)); /* Check for EINTR */
7431  }
7432 
7433  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(ferror(source_file) != 0 || FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FERROR(destination_file) != 0))
7434  {
7435  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FCLOSE(source_file); // No need to error check here because already going
7436  // wrong.
7437  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FCLOSE(destination_file); // No need to error check here because already
7438  // going wrong.
7439 
7440  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7441  return -1;
7442  }
7443 
7444  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(fclose(source_file) != 0 || FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FCLOSE(destination_file) != 0)) // Error check
7445  {
7446  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7447  return -1;
7448  }
7449 
7450  return 0;
7451 }

7453 #ifdef _WIN32
7454 #include <windows.h>
7455 
7475 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char **list_files_with_pattern(const char *directory, const char *pattern, size_t *len)
7476 {
7477  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(directory);
7478  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(pattern);
7479  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(len);
7480 
7481  *len = 0;
7482  char search_path[MAX_PATH];
7483  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_SNPRINTF(search_path, MAX_PATH, "%s\\%s", directory, pattern);
7484 
7485  WIN32_FIND_DATA find_file_data;
7486  HANDLE find_handle = FindFirstFile(search_path, &find_file_data);
7487 
7488  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(find_handle == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE))
7489  {
7490 
7491  /* One element of size zero. */
7492  char **new_array = (char **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(sizeof(char *));
7493  *new_array = NULL;
7494  return new_array;
7495  }
7496 
7497  /* Count the number of files matching the pattern */
7498  int file_count = 0;
7499  do
7500  {
7501  if (!(find_file_data.dwFileAttributes & FILE_ATTRIBUTE_DIRECTORY))
7502  {
7503  ++file_count;
7504  }
7505  } while (FindNextFile(find_handle, &find_file_data) != 0);
7506 
7507  size_t mul;
7508 
7509  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(file_count == 0))
7510  {
7511  mul = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_INITIAL_STRING_ARRAY_ALLOC_SIZE;
7512  }
7513  else if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul_ptr(file_count, sizeof(char *), &mul) == 0))
7514  {
7515  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7516  return NULL;
7517  }
7518 
7519  /* Allocate memory for the array of strings */
7520  char **files_array = (char **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(mul);
7521  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(files_array == NULL))
7522  {
7523  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7524  return NULL;
7525  }
7526 
7527  /* Populate the array with file names matching the pattern */
7528  int index = 0;
7529  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(FindClose(find_handle) == 0))
7530  {
7531  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7532  return NULL;
7533  }
7534  find_handle = FindFirstFile(search_path, &find_file_data);
7535  do
7536  {
7537  if (!(find_file_data.dwFileAttributes & FILE_ATTRIBUTE_DIRECTORY))
7538  {
7539  files_array[index] = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_STRDUP(find_file_data.cFileName);
7540  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(files_array[index] == NULL))
7541  {
7542  return NULL;
7543  }
7544  ++index;
7545  }
7546  } while (FindNextFile(find_handle, &find_file_data) != 0);
7547 
7548  /* Close the find handle */
7549  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(FindClose(find_handle) == 0))
7550  {
7551  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7552  return NULL;
7553  }
7554 
7555  *len = index;
7556 
7557  return files_array;
7558 }
7559 
7560 #else
7561 
7562 #include <dirent.h>
7563 #include <fnmatch.h>
7564 
7584 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char **list_files_with_pattern(const char *directory, const char *pattern, size_t *len)
7585 {
7586  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(directory);
7587  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(pattern);
7588  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(len);
7589 
7590  *len = 0;
7591  DIR *dir = opendir(directory);
7592  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(dir == NULL))
7593  {
7594  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7595  return NULL;
7596  }
7597 
7598  /* Count the number of files matching the pattern */
7599  int file_count = 0;
7600  struct dirent *entry;
7601  while ((entry = readdir(dir)) != NULL)
7602  {
7603  if (fnmatch(pattern, entry->d_name, FNM_PERIOD) == 0)
7604  {
7605  ++file_count;
7606  }
7607  }
7608 
7609  rewinddir(dir); // No errors with this function
7610 
7611  size_t mul;
7612 
7613  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(file_count == 0))
7614  {
7615  mul = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_INITIAL_STRING_ARRAY_ALLOC_SIZE;
7616  }
7617  else if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul_ptr(file_count, sizeof(char *), &mul) == 0))
7618  {
7619  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7620  return NULL;
7621  }
7622 
7623  /* Allocate memory for the array of strings */
7624  char **files_array = (char **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(mul);
7625 
7626  /* Populate the array with file names matching the pattern */
7627  size_t index = 0;
7628  while ((entry = readdir(dir)) != NULL)
7629  {
7630  if (fnmatch(pattern, entry->d_name, FNM_PERIOD) == 0)
7631  {
7632  files_array[index] = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_STRDUP(entry->d_name);
7633  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(files_array[index] == NULL))
7634  {
7635  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7636  return NULL;
7637  }
7638  ++index;
7639  }
7640  }
7641  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(closedir(dir) == -1))
7642  {
7643  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7644  return NULL;
7645  }
7646 
7647  *len = index;
7648 
7649  return files_array;
7650 }
7651 
7652 #endif
7653 
7670 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *concatenate_string_array(const char **strings, size_t num_strings)
7671 {
7672  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(strings);
7673 
7674  /* Initialize total length and allocate initial memory for result */
7675  size_t alloc_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_INITIAL_STRING_ARRAY_ALLOC_SIZE;
7676  char *result = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(alloc_size);
7677 
7678  // Check for initial memory allocation failure
7679  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result == NULL))
7680  goto memory_error;
7681 
7682  size_t new_len;
7683 
7684  // If no strings, new_len will still be 0, and then a null terminator will be put at byte 0.
7685  new_len = 0;
7686 
7687  // Concatenate the strings char by char using FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY and FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_REALLOC
7688  for (size_t i = 0; i < num_strings; ++i)
7689  {
7690  const char *current_string = strings[i];
7691 
7692  // Iterate through each character and append to the result
7693  size_t current_length_of_current_string = 0;
7694  while (current_string[current_length_of_current_string] != '\0')
7695  {
7696  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_len == SIZE_MAX))
7697  goto overflow;
7698  /* FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_REALLOC_REALLOCATION_ALGORITHM returns always at least one more */
7699  const size_t new_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_REALLOC_REALLOCATION_ALGORITHM(new_len + sizeof("")); /* Safe. */
7700 
7701  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_size == 0))
7702  {
7703  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(result);
7704  goto memory_error;
7705  }
7706  // Resize the result string if necessary
7707  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_size > alloc_size))
7708  {
7709  char *new_result = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_REALLOC(result, new_size);
7710 
7711  // Check for realloc failure
7712  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_result == NULL))
7713  {
7714  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(result);
7715  goto memory_error;
7716  }
7717 
7718  result = new_result;
7719  }
7720 
7721  // Append the current character to the result
7722  result[new_len++] = current_string[current_length_of_current_string++];
7723  }
7724  }
7725 
7726  // Add the null terminator
7727  result[new_len] = '\0';
7728 
7729  return result;
7730 
7731 overflow:
7732 memory_error:
7733  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7734  return NULL;
7735 }
7736 
7751 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *concatenate_strings(const char *str1, const char *str2)
7752 {
7753  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(str1);
7754  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(str2);
7755 
7756  const char *strs[2] = {str1, str2};
7757 
7758  return concatenate_string_array(strs, 2);
7759 }

7801 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int replace_memory(void *source, size_t source_len, void *find, size_t find_len, void *replace, size_t replace_len, void **output, size_t *output_length_without_nullt, int *should_free_after_use, size_t matches_max /* 0 for unlimited replacement */, size_t *num_matches_found, int should_nullt)
7802 {
7803  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(source);
7804  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(find);
7805  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(replace);
7806  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(output);
7807  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(output_length_without_nullt);
7808  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(should_free_after_use);
7809  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(num_matches_found);
7810 
7811  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(find_len == 0))
7812  goto no_matches;
7813 
7814  size_t matches;
7815 
7816  matches = 0;
7817 
7818  // Count the occurrences of 'find' in 'source'
7819  const char *p;
7820 
7821  p = (const char *)source;
7822 
7823  const char *end_of_memory;
7824  end_of_memory = (const char *)source + source_len;
7825 
7826  for (;;)
7827  {
7828  if ((p = (const char *)memory_locate((const void *)p, (end_of_memory - p), find, find_len)) == NULL)
7829  break;
7830  if (matches_max && matches == matches_max)
7831  break;
7832 
7833  ++matches;
7834  p += find_len;
7835  }
7836 
7837  // Let's assume that it's 'likely' to find a match.
7838  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(matches == 0))
7839  {
7840  no_matches:
7841  *should_free_after_use = 0;
7842  *output_length_without_nullt = source_len;
7843  *output = source;
7844  return 0;
7845  }
7846 
7847  *should_free_after_use = 1;
7848  *num_matches_found = matches;
7849 
7850  size_t final_len = source_len - matches * find_len + matches * replace_len; // Overflow should not be an issue here.
7851 
7852  if (should_nullt)
7853  {
7854  ++final_len;
7855  }
7856 
7857  // Allocate memory for the replaced string
7858  char *result;
7859 
7860  result = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(final_len);
7861  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result == NULL))
7862  {
7863  goto memory_error;
7864  }
7865  *output_length_without_nullt = final_len;
7866 
7867  *output = result;
7868 
7869  // Perform the replacement
7870  char *rp;
7871 
7872  rp = result;
7873 
7874  p = (const char *)source;
7875 
7876  matches = 0;
7877 
7878  // If matches is 0, this is not run.
7879  for (matches = 0; !matches_max || (matches < matches_max); ++matches)
7880  {
7881  if ((p = (const char *)memory_locate((const void *)p, end_of_memory - p, find, find_len)) == NULL)
7882  break;
7883 
7884  if (matches_max && matches == matches_max)
7885  break;
7886 
7887  size_t prefix_len = p - (const char *)source;
7888  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY(rp, source, prefix_len);
7889  rp += prefix_len;
7890  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY(rp, replace, replace_len);
7891  rp += replace_len;
7892  p += find_len;
7893  source = (void *)p;
7894  }
7895 
7896  // Copy the remaining part of the source string
7897  size_t remaining_len;
7898 
7899  remaining_len = end_of_memory - (const char *)source;
7900  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY(rp, source, remaining_len);
7901 
7902  if (should_nullt)
7903  {
7904  rp[remaining_len] = '\0';
7905  }
7906 
7907  return 0;
7908 
7909 memory_error:
7910  *output = NULL;
7911  *output_length_without_nullt = 0;
7912  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7913  return -1;
7914 }
7915 
7957 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int replace_all_with_lens(const char *source, size_t source_len, const char *find, size_t find_len, const char *replace, size_t replace_len, char **output, size_t *new_len, int *should_free_after_use, size_t matches_max, size_t *num_matches)
7958 {
7959  /* replace_memory checks args if enabled. */
7960  return replace_memory((void *)source, source_len, (void *)find, find_len, (void *)replace, replace_len, (void **)output, new_len, should_free_after_use, matches_max, num_matches, 1);
7961 }

7977 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *replace_all(const char *source, const char *find, const char *replace)
7978 {
7979  /* replace_memory checks args if enabled. */
7980 
7981  size_t new_len;
7982  char *output;
7983  int should_free_after_use;
7984  size_t num_matches;
7985  const size_t matches_max = 0;
7986 
7987  if (replace_memory((void *)source, strlen(source), (void *)find, strlen(find), (void *)replace, strlen(replace), (void **)&output, &new_len, &should_free_after_use, matches_max, &num_matches, 1) == -1)
7988  {
7989  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7990  return NULL;
7991  }
7992 
7993  if (!should_free_after_use)
7994  {
7995  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_len == SIZE_MAX))
7996  {
7997  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
7998  return NULL;
7999  }
8000 
8001  char *new_output = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(new_len + 1); /* Safe. */
8002  memcpy(new_output, output, new_len + 1); /* It was already null terminated */
8003  return new_output;
8004  }
8005 
8006  return output;
8007 }

8117 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *replace_all_with_callback(const char *str, const char *old_substring, char *(*callback)(const char *, void *), void *data_for_callback)
8118 {
8119  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(str);
8120  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(old_substring);
8121  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(callback);
8122 
8123  const size_t str_len = strlen(str);
8124  const size_t old_substring_len = strlen(old_substring);
8125  size_t alloc_size = str_len + 1; // Start with the original string length + 1 for the null terminator
8126 
8127  // Allocate memory for the result string
8128  char *result = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(str_len);
8129  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result == NULL))
8130  {
8131  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
8132  return NULL;
8133  }
8134 
8135  // Copy and replace substrings
8136  const char *pos = str;
8137 
8138  size_t new_len = 0;
8139 
8140  for (;;)
8141  {
8142  const char *found_pos = (const char *)memory_locate(pos, str_len - (pos - str), old_substring, old_substring_len);
8143  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(found_pos == NULL))
8144  {
8145  size_t remaining_len = str_len - (pos - str);
8146  memcpy(result + new_len, pos, remaining_len);
8147  new_len += remaining_len;
8148 
8149  result[new_len] = '\0';
8150 
8151  new_len += remaining_len;
8152  break;
8153  }
8154 
8155  // Copy the segment
8156 
8157  char *replacement = callback(old_substring, data_for_callback);
8158 
8159  // Resize the result buffer if needed
8160  size_t replacement_len = strlen(replacement);
8161 
8162  size_t nlen;
8163 
8164  const size_t diff = found_pos - pos;
8165 
8166  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_3_ptr(new_len, diff, replacement_len, &nlen) == 0))
8167  {
8168  goto overflow;
8169  }
8170 
8171  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(nlen == SIZE_MAX))
8172  goto overflow;
8173 
8174  ++nlen;
8175 
8176  if (nlen >= alloc_size)
8177  {
8178  /* Makes it at least 1 bigger. */
8179  alloc_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_REALLOC_REALLOCATION_ALGORITHM(nlen);
8180  char *new_result = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_REALLOC(result, alloc_size);
8181  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_result == NULL))
8182  {
8183  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(replacement);
8184  goto error;
8185  }
8186  result = new_result;
8187  }
8188 
8189  memcpy(result + new_len, pos, found_pos - pos); /* Safe. */
8190  new_len += found_pos - pos;
8191  memcpy(result + new_len, replacement, replacement_len);
8192  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(replacement);
8193  new_len += replacement_len;
8194  pos = found_pos + old_substring_len;
8195  }
8196 
8197  return result;
8198 overflow:
8199 
8200 error:
8201  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(result);
8202  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
8203  return NULL;
8204 }

8220 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *dup_format(const char *format, ...)
8221 {
8222  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(format);
8223 
8224  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_VA_LIST args;
8225  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_VA_START(args, format);
8226 
8227  /* Determine the length of the formatted string */
8228  const int len = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_VSNPRINTF(NULL, 0, format, args);
8229 
8230  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_VA_END(args);
8231 
8232  if (len == -1)
8233  goto memory_error;
8234 
8235  /* Would-be Overflow */
8236  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(sizeof(int) >= sizeof(size_t) && (size_t)len == SIZE_MAX))
8237  goto memory_error;
8238 
8239  /* Allocate memory for the formatted string */
8240  char *result;
8241 
8242  result = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(len + sizeof("")); /* Safe */
8243  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result == NULL))
8244  goto memory_error;
8245 
8246  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_VA_START(args, format);
8247  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_VSNPRINTF(result, len + 1, format, args) == -1)
8248  {
8249  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(result);
8250  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_VA_END(args);
8251  goto memory_error;
8252  }
8253 
8254  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_VA_END(args);
8255 
8256  return result;
8257 
8258 memory_error:
8259  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
8260  return NULL;
8261 }

8476 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void reduce(void *array, size_t size, size_t elem_size, void *result, void (*operation)(void *, void *))
8477 {
8478  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array);
8479  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(result);
8480  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(operation);
8481 
8482  char *char_array = (char *)array;
8483  char *char_result = (char *)result;
8484 
8485  /* Initialize the result with the first element */
8486  for (size_t i = 0; i < elem_size; ++i)
8487  {
8488  char_result[i] = char_array[i];
8489  }
8490 
8491  for (size_t i = 1; i < size; ++i)
8492  {
8493  operation(char_result, char_array + i * elem_size);
8494  }
8495 }

8497 // filter_data() to avoid conflicts with curses
8498 
8540 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC size_t filter_data(void *source, size_t source_size, size_t elem_size, void *destination, size_t dest_size, int (*condition)(void *))
8541 {
8542  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(source);
8543  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(destination);
8544  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(condition);
8545 
8546  char *char_source = (char *)source;
8547  char *char_destination = (char *)destination;
8548 
8549  size_t count = 0;
8550  for (size_t i = 0; i < source_size; ++i)
8551  {
8552  if (condition(char_source + i * elem_size))
8553  {
8554  if (count < dest_size)
8555  {
8556  for (size_t j = 0; j < elem_size; ++j)
8557  {
8558  char_destination[count * elem_size + j] = char_source[i * elem_size + j];
8559  }
8560  }
8561 
8562  ++count;
8563  }
8564  }
8565  return count;
8566 }

8656 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void *list_comprehension(const void *input_array, size_t array_size, size_t elem_size, void (*transform_func)(void *value), int (*filter_func)(void *value), size_t *result_size)
8657 {
8658  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(input_array);
8659  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(transform_func);
8660  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(filter_func);
8661 
8662  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(result_size);
8663 
8664  // Set result size to 0 first thing.
8665  *result_size = 0;
8666 
8667  const size_t alloc_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(array_size, elem_size);
8668 
8669  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(alloc_size == 0))
8670  {
8671  /* Handle overflow error. */
8672  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
8673  return NULL;
8674  }
8675 
8676  /* Allocate memory for the result array */
8677  void *result = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(alloc_size);
8678 
8679  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result == NULL))
8680  {
8681  /* Handle memory allocation error */
8682  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
8683  return NULL;
8684  }
8685 
8686  /* Iterate through the input array */
8687  for (size_t i = 0; i < array_size; ++i)
8688  {
8689  /* Apply the filter function */
8690 
8691  // Assume that there cannot be an overflow error
8692  // because iterating through a size_t array from 0.
8693  if (filter_func((void *)((char *)input_array + i * elem_size)))
8694  {
8695  /* Apply the transformation function */
8696 
8697  void *addr = (char *)result + (*result_size) * elem_size;
8698  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY(addr, (char *)input_array + (i * elem_size), elem_size); /* Safe. */
8699  transform_func(addr);
8700  ++(*result_size);
8701  }
8702  }
8703 
8704  // We need this so that gcc with -std=c11 under mingw32 doesn't give a
8705  // warning about memory possibly being accessed after freeing()
8706  // This only seems to happen with mingw32, and is a bug in it.
8707  // I included a relevant ISO/IEC statement about realloc in this file.
8708  //
8709  // This code has no bug.
8710 
8711  /*
8712  * Make the result smaller to free a bit of memory. Not necessary, but it saves memory.
8713  * array_size * (*result_size) will not be larger than the current size.
8714  *
8715  * Dont do safe mul here because this should be smaller than current amounts.
8716  */
8717  char *new_result = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_REALLOC(result, array_size * (*result_size)); /* Safe. */
8718 
8719  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_result == NULL))
8720  {
8721  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
8722  return result;
8723  }
8724 
8725  /*
8726  ISO/IEC 9899:2011:
8727 
8728  "If memory for the new object cannot be allocated,
8729  the old object is not deallocated and its value is unchanged."
8730  */
8731 
8732  return new_result;
8733 }
