8786 
8787 #if FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_THREAD_FUNCTIONS_ENABLED
8788 #include <threads.h>
8789 
8790 // Define a structure to hold thread-specific data
8791 struct ThreadData
8792 {
8793  const void *input_array;
8794  size_t array_size;
8795  size_t elem_size;
8796  void (*transform_func)(void *value);
8797  int (*filter_func)(void *value);
8798  size_t *result_size;
8799  void *result;
8800  size_t start_index;
8801  size_t end_index;
8802 };
8803 
8804 /*
8805  * Define the worker function for each thread, as used by
8806  * list_comprehension_multithreaded()
8807  */
8808 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_list_comprehension_worker(void *data)
8809 {
8810  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(data);
8811  struct ThreadData *thread_data = (struct ThreadData *)data;
8812  *thread_data->result_size = 0;
8813 
8814  const size_t subtraction = (thread_data->end_index - thread_data->start_index);
8815 
8816  const size_t mul = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(thread_data->elem_size, subtraction);
8817 
8818  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(mul == 0)) // Overflow
8819  {
8820  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
8821  return -1;
8822  }
8823 
8824  void *buffer = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(mul);
8825 
8826  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(buffer == NULL))
8827  {
8828  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
8829  return -1;
8830  }
8831 
8832  // Iterate through the assigned chunk of the input array
8833 
8834  // Start index and end index should be valid indices and no possiblity
8835  // for overflow error.
8836  for (size_t i = thread_data->start_index; i < thread_data->end_index; ++i)
8837  {
8838  // Apply the filter function
8839  if (thread_data->filter_func((void *)((char *)thread_data->input_array + i * thread_data->elem_size)))
8840  {
8841  // Copy the value to the result array
8842  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY((char *)buffer + (*thread_data->result_size) * thread_data->elem_size, (char *)thread_data->input_array + i * thread_data->elem_size, thread_data->elem_size); /* Safe. */
8843 
8844  ++(*thread_data->result_size);
8845  }
8846  }
8847 
8848  // Apply the transformation function to the entire result chunk
8849  for (size_t i = 0; i < (*thread_data->result_size); ++i)
8850  {
8851  thread_data->transform_func((void *)((char *)buffer + i * thread_data->elem_size));
8852  }
8853 
8854  thread_data->result = buffer;
8855  return 0;
8856 }
8857 
8876 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void *list_comprehension_multithreaded(const void *input_array, size_t array_size, size_t elem_size, void (*transform_func)(void *value), int (*filter_func)(void *value), size_t *result_size, size_t thread_count)
8877 {
8878  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(input_array);
8879  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(transform_func);
8880  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(filter_func);
8881  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(result_size);
8882 
8883  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(thread_count == 0))
8884  {
8885  // This doesn't make sense, so assume they mean 1.
8886  thread_count = 1;
8887  }
8888 
8889  // Set result size to 0 first thing.
8890  *result_size = 0;
8891 
8892  const size_t alloc_size_for_result = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(array_size, elem_size);
8893 
8894  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(alloc_size_for_result == 0))
8895  {
8896  /* Handle overflow error. */
8897  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
8898  return NULL;
8899  }
8900 
8901  /* Allocate memory for the result array */
8902  void *result = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(alloc_size_for_result);
8903 
8904  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result == NULL))
8905  {
8906  /* Handle memory allocation error */
8907  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
8908  return NULL;
8909  }
8910 
8911  /* Allocate memory for result sizes */
8912 
8913  const size_t alloc_size_for_thread_result_sizes = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(thread_count, sizeof(size_t));
8914  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(alloc_size_for_thread_result_sizes == 0))
8915  {
8916  /* Handle overflow error. */
8917  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(result);
8918  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
8919  return NULL;
8920  }
8921 
8922  size_t *thread_result_sizes = (size_t *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(alloc_size_for_thread_result_sizes);
8923  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(thread_result_sizes == NULL))
8924  {
8925  // Handle memory allocation error
8926  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(result);
8927  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
8928  return NULL;
8929  }
8930 
8931  const size_t alloc_size_for_threads = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(thread_count, sizeof(thrd_t));
8932  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(alloc_size_for_threads == 0))
8933  {
8934  /* Handle overflow error. */
8935  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(result);
8936  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(thread_result_sizes);
8937  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
8938  return NULL;
8939  }
8940 
8941  // Initialize thread data
8942  thrd_t *threads = (thrd_t *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(alloc_size_for_threads);
8943  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(threads == NULL))
8944  {
8945  // Handle memory allocation error
8946  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(result);
8947  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(thread_result_sizes);
8948  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
8949  return NULL;
8950  }
8951  const size_t alloc_size_for_thread_data = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(thread_count, sizeof(struct ThreadData));
8952  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(alloc_size_for_thread_data == 0))
8953  {
8954  /* Handle overflow error. */
8955  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(result);
8956  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(thread_result_sizes);
8957  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
8958  return NULL;
8959  }
8960  struct ThreadData *thread_data = (struct ThreadData *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(alloc_size_for_thread_data);
8961  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(thread_data == NULL))
8962  {
8963  cannot_allocate_or_create:
8964  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(result);
8965  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(thread_result_sizes);
8966 
8967  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(threads);
8968 
8969  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
8970  return NULL;
8971  }
8972 
8973  // Divide the input array into chunks for each thread
8974  size_t chunk_size = array_size / thread_count;
8975  size_t remaining = array_size % thread_count;
8976  size_t current_index = 0;
8977 
8978  for (size_t i = 0; i < thread_count; ++i)
8979  {
8980  size_t e_index;
8981  const size_t ret = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_3_ptr(current_index, chunk_size, (remaining > 0 ? 1 : 0), &e_index);
8982 
8983  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(ret == 0))
8984  goto cannot_allocate_or_create; // Overflow
8985 
8986  thread_data[i].input_array = input_array;
8987  thread_data[i].array_size = array_size;
8988  thread_data[i].elem_size = elem_size;
8989  thread_data[i].transform_func = transform_func;
8990  thread_data[i].filter_func = filter_func;
8991  thread_data[i].result_size = &thread_result_sizes[i];
8992  thread_data[i].result = result;
8993  thread_data[i].start_index = current_index;
8994  thread_data[i].end_index = e_index;
8995 
8996  if (remaining > 0)
8997  {
8998  --remaining;
8999  }
9000 
9001  current_index = thread_data[i].end_index;
9002 
9003  // Create a thread for each chunk
9004  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(thrd_create(&threads[i], FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_list_comprehension_worker, (void *)&thread_data[i]) != thrd_success))
9005  goto cannot_allocate_or_create;
9006  }
9007 
9008  // Wait for all threads to finish
9009  for (size_t i = 0; i < thread_count; ++i)
9010  {
9011  int return_value_of_thread;
9012  thrd_join(threads[i], &return_value_of_thread);
9013 
9014  // The thread failed.
9015  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(return_value_of_thread == -1))
9016  goto cannot_allocate_or_create;
9017  }
9018  // Calculate the total result size
9019  size_t total_result_size = 0;
9020  for (size_t i = 0; i < thread_count; ++i)
9021  {
9022  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY((char *)result + total_result_size * elem_size, thread_data[i].result, thread_result_sizes[i] * elem_size); /* Safe. */
9023  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(thread_data[i].result);
9024 
9025  // Should always be <= SIZE_MAX
9026  total_result_size += thread_result_sizes[i];
9027  }
9028 
9029  // Update the final result size
9030  *result_size = total_result_size;
9031 
9032  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(thread_result_sizes);
9033  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(thread_data);
9034  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(threads);
9035 
9036  return result;
9037 }
9038 
9039 #endif
9040 
9059 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void *reject_array(const void *source, size_t source_size, size_t elem_size, int (*condition)(const void *), size_t *result_size)
9060 {
9061 
9062  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(source);
9063  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(condition);
9064 
9065  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(result_size);
9066  *result_size = 0;
9067  /* Allocate memory for the result array */
9068 
9069  const size_t mul = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(source_size, elem_size);
9070  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(mul == 0))
9071  {
9072  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
9073  return NULL;
9074  }
9075 
9076  void *result = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(mul);
9077  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result == NULL))
9078  {
9079  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
9080  return NULL;
9081  }
9082 
9083  size_t result_index = 0;
9084 
9085  /* Apply the rejection condition to each element */
9086  for (size_t i = 0; i < source_size; ++i)
9087  {
9088  // Should be a valid index if passed a valid argument.
9089  const void *current_source = (char *)source + i * elem_size;
9090 
9091  /* Check condition */
9092  if (!condition(current_source))
9093  {
9094  void *current_result = (char *)result + result_index * elem_size;
9095  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY(current_result, current_source, elem_size);
9096  result_index++;
9097  }
9098  }
9099 
9100  /* Set the result size */
9101  *result_size = result_index;
9102 
9103  return result;
9104 }
9105 
9124 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void *select_array(const void *source, size_t source_size, size_t elem_size, int (*condition)(const void *), size_t *result_size)
9125 {
9126 
9127  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(source);
9128 
9129  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(condition);
9130  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(result_size);
9131 
9132  *result_size = 0;
9133  /* Allocate memory for the result array */
9134 
9135  const size_t mul = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(source_size, elem_size);
9136  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(mul == 0))
9137  {
9138  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
9139  return NULL;
9140  }
9141 
9142  void *result = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(mul);
9143  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result == NULL))
9144  {
9145  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
9146  return NULL;
9147  }
9148 
9149  size_t result_index = 0;
9150 
9151  /* Apply the selection condition to each element */
9152  for (size_t i = 0; i < source_size; ++i)
9153  {
9154  const void *current_source = (char *)source + i * elem_size;
9155 
9156  /* Check condition */
9157  if (condition(current_source))
9158  {
9159  void *current_result = (char *)result + result_index * elem_size;
9160  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY(current_result, current_source, elem_size);
9161  ++result_index;
9162  }
9163  }
9164 
9165  /* Set the result size */
9166  *result_size = result_index;
9167 
9168  return result;
9169 }

9186 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void *replicate(const void *source, size_t source_size, size_t elem_size, size_t repetitions)
9187 {
9188 
9189  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(source);
9190 
9191  /* elem_size * source_size * repetitions */
9192 
9193  const size_t elem_times_source = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(elem_size, source_size);
9194  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(elem_times_source == 0))
9195  {
9196  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
9197  return NULL;
9198  }
9199 
9200  const size_t result_total_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(elem_times_source, repetitions);
9201  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result_total_size == 0))
9202  {
9203  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
9204  return NULL;
9205  }
9206 
9207  /* Allocate memory for the result array */
9208  void *result = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(result_total_size);
9209  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result == NULL))
9210  {
9211  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
9212  return NULL;
9213  }
9214 
9215  /* Copy the source array to the result array multiple times */
9216  for (size_t i = 0; i < repetitions; ++i)
9217  {
9218  // Counting from zero so it should not be an overflow.
9219  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMCPY((char *)result + (i * elem_times_source), source, elem_times_source); /* Safe. */
9220  }
9221 
9222  return result;
9223 }

9239 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *string_to_lowercase(char *string)
9240 {
9241 
9242  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(string);
9243 
9244  char *new_str = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_STRDUP(string);
9245 
9246  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_str == NULL))
9247  {
9248  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
9249  return NULL;
9250  }
9251  char *orig_str = new_str;
9252  while (*new_str)
9253  {
9254  *new_str = tolower(*new_str);
9255  ++new_str;
9256  }
9257 
9258  return orig_str;
9259 }

9605 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int string_array_uniq(const char **array, size_t size, char ***output, size_t *output_size)
9606 {
9607  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array);
9608 
9609  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(output);
9610  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(output_size);
9611 
9612  *output_size = 0;
9613 
9614  const size_t alloc_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(size, sizeof(char *));
9615 
9616  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(alloc_size == 0))
9617  {
9618  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
9619  return -1;
9620  }
9621 
9622  // Count the number of unique strings
9623  size_t count = 0;
9624 
9625  // Allocate memory for the array to store unique strings
9626  *output = (char **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(alloc_size);
9627  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(*output == NULL))
9628  {
9629  // Memory allocation failed
9630  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
9631  return -1;
9632  }
9633 
9634  // Initialize all elements to NULL
9635  for (size_t i = 0; i < size; ++i)
9636  {
9637  (*output)[i] = NULL;
9638  }
9639 
9640  // Iterate through the input array to find unique strings
9641  for (size_t i = 0; i < size; ++i)
9642  {
9643  int is_unique = 1;
9644 
9645  // Check if the current string is not equal to any previous strings
9646  for (size_t j = 0; j < count; ++j)
9647  {
9648  if ((*output)[j] != NULL && FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRCMP(array[i], (*output)[j]) == 0)
9649  {
9650  is_unique = 0; // Not unique
9651  break;
9652  }
9653  }
9654 
9655  if (is_unique)
9656  {
9657  (*output)[count] = ((char **)array)[i]; // No strdup used.
9658 
9659  ++count;
9660  }
9661  }
9662 
9663  // Set the output size
9664  *output_size = count;
9665 
9666  return 0;
9667 }
9668 
9705 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int string_array_uniq_adjacent(const char **first_array, size_t size, char ***new_array, size_t *new_size)
9706 {
9707  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(first_array);
9708 
9709  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(new_array);
9710  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(new_size);
9711 
9712  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(first_array);
9713  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(new_array);
9714  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(new_size);
9715 
9716  *new_size = 0;
9717  const size_t alloc_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(size, sizeof(char *));
9718 
9719  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(alloc_size == 0))
9720  {
9721  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
9722  return -1;
9723  }
9724 
9725  // Create a new dynamically allocated array
9726  *new_array = (char **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(alloc_size);
9727  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(*new_array == NULL))
9728  {
9729  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
9730  return -1;
9731  }
9732 
9733  // Remove adjacent duplicates from arr1 and copy to arr2
9734  for (size_t i = 0; i < size; ++i)
9735  {
9736  if (i == 0 || FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRCMP(first_array[i], first_array[i - 1]) != 0)
9737  {
9738  (*new_array)[(*new_size)++] = (char *)first_array[i]; // No strdup
9739  }
9740  }
9741 
9742  return 0;
9743 }

9868 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int map_filesystem_files_as_strings(const char *directory, char *(*map_function)(const char *file_string_data, size_t string_size))
9869 {
9870 
9871  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(directory);
9872  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(map_function);
9873 
9874 #ifdef _WIN32
9875  WIN32_FIND_DATA findFileData;
9876  HANDLE hFind = FindFirstFile(directory, &findFileData);
9877 
9878  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(hFind == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE))
9879  {
9880  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
9881  return -1;
9882  }
9883 
9884  do
9885  {
9886  if (!(findFileData.dwFileAttributes & FILE_ATTRIBUTE_DIRECTORY))
9887  {
9888  // Regular file
9889  char *file_data;
9890  size_t size;
9891 
9892  // Get the regular file.
9893  char fullFilePath[MAX_PATH];
9894  _stprintf(fullFilePath, _T("%s%c%s"), directory, FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_DIR_SEPARATOR, findFileData.cFileName);
9895 
9896  file_data = read_file_into_string(fullFilePath, &size);
9897  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(file_data == NULL))
9898  {
9899  // No need to re-die aggressively.
9900  FindClose(hFind); /* No need to error check here because there already is an error. */
9901  return -1;
9902  }
9903 
9904  // The result of the map operation
9905  const char *new_str = map_function(file_data, size);
9906 
9907  // Write the result to disk
9908  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(write_file(fullFilePath, new_str) == -1))
9909  {
9910  // No need to re-die aggressively.
9911  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(file_data);
9912  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE((char *)new_str);
9913  FindClose(hFind); // No need to error check here because there already is an error.
9914  return -1;
9915  }
9916 
9917  // Free memory.
9918  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(file_data);
9919  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE((char *)new_str);
9920  }
9921 
9922  } while (FindNextFile(hFind, &findFileData) != 0);
9923 
9924  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(FindClose(hFind) == 0))
9925  {
9926  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
9927  return -1;
9928  }
9929 
9930 #else
9931  DIR *dir = opendir(directory);
9932  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(dir == NULL))
9933  {
9934  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
9935  return -1;
9936  }
9937 
9938  struct dirent *entry;
9939  while ((entry = readdir(dir)) != NULL)
9940  {
9941  if (entry->d_type == DT_REG)
9942  { // Regular file
9943  char *file_data;
9944  size_t size;
9945 
9946  // Get the regular file.
9947  char fullFilePath[PATH_MAX];
9948  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_SNPRINTF(fullFilePath, PATH_MAX, "%s%c%s", directory, FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_DIR_SEPARATOR, entry->d_name);
9949 
9950  file_data = read_file_into_string(fullFilePath, &size);
9951  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(file_data == NULL))
9952  {
9953  // No need to re-die aggressively.
9954  return -1;
9955  }
9956 
9957  // The result of the map operation
9958  const char *new_str = map_function(file_data, size);
9959 
9960  // Write the result to disk
9961  if (write_file(fullFilePath, new_str) == -1)
9962  {
9963  // No need to re-die aggressively.
9964  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(file_data);
9965  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE((char *)new_str);
9966  return -1;
9967  }
9968 
9969  // Free memory.
9970  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(file_data);
9971  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE((char *)new_str);
9972  }
9973  }
9974 
9975  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(closedir(dir) == -1))
9976  {
9977  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
9978  return -1;
9979  }
9980 
9981 #endif
9982 
9983  return 0;
9984 }

10057

10059  {
10060  // Handle error or return -1
10061  if (closedir(dir) == -1)
10062  {
10063  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
10064  return -1;
10065  }
10066  return -1;
10067  }
10068  }
10069  }
10070  }
10071 
10072  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(closedir(dir) == -1))
10073  {
10074  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();

10076  }
10077 #endif

10103 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *reduce_filesystem_files_as_strings(const char *directory, const char *out_file, char *(*reduce_function)(char *value1, ...))
10104 {
10105  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(directory);
10106  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(out_file);
10107  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(reduce_function);
10108 #ifdef _WIN32
10109  WIN32_FIND_DATA findFileData;
10110  HANDLE hFind = FindFirstFile(directory, &findFileData);
10111 
10112  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(hFind == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE))
10113  {
10114  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
10115  return NULL;
10116  }
10117 
10118  char *last_value = NULL;
10119  char *value = NULL;
10120 
10121  do
10122  {
10123  if (!(findFileData.dwFileAttributes & FILE_ATTRIBUTE_DIRECTORY) && findFileData.dwFileAttributes & FILE_ATTRIBUTE_NORMAL)
10124  {
10125  // Regular file
10126  size_t size;
10127 
10128  // Get the regular file.
10129  char fullFilePath[MAX_PATH];
10130  _stprintf(fullFilePath, _T("%s%c%s"), directory, FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_DIR_SEPARATOR, findFileData.cFileName);
10131 
10132  value = read_file_into_string(fullFilePath, &size);
10133  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(value == NULL))
10134  {
10135  // No need to re-die aggressively.
10136  FindClose(hFind); /* Don't need to care about the return value because there already is an error. */
10137  return NULL;
10138  }
10139 
10140  char *new_value = reduce_function(last_value, value, findFileData.cFileName);
10141  if (last_value)
10142  {
10143  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(last_value);
10144  }
10145 
10146  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(value);
10147  last_value = new_value;
10148 
10149  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(remove_file(fullFilePath) == -1))
10150  {
10151  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
10152  return NULL;
10153  }
10154  }
10155 
10156  } while (FindNextFile(hFind, &findFileData) != 0);
10157 
10158  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(FindClose(hFind) == 0))
10159  {
10160  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
10161  return NULL;
10162  }
10163 #else
10164  DIR *dir = opendir(directory);
10165  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(dir == NULL))
10166  {
10167  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
10168  return NULL;
10169  }
10170 
10171  char *last_value = NULL;
10172  char *value = NULL;
10173  struct dirent *entry;
10174 
10175  while ((entry = readdir(dir)) != NULL)
10176  {
10177  if (entry->d_type == DT_REG)
10178  {
10179  // Regular file
10180  size_t size;
10181 
10182  // Get the regular file.
10183  char fullFilePath[PATH_MAX];
10184  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_SNPRINTF(fullFilePath, PATH_MAX, "%s%c%s", directory, FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_DIR_SEPARATOR, entry->d_name);
10185 
10186  value = read_file_into_string(fullFilePath, &size);
10187  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(value == NULL))
10188  {
10189  // No need to re-die aggressively.
10190  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(closedir(dir) == -1))
10191  {
10192  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
10193  return NULL;
10194  }
10195  return NULL;
10196  }
10197 
10198  char *new_value = reduce_function(last_value, value, entry->d_name);
10199  if (last_value)
10200  {
10201  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(last_value);
10202  }
10203 
10204  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(value);
10205  last_value = new_value;
10206 
10207  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(remove_file(fullFilePath) == -1))
10208  {
10209  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
10210  return NULL;
10211  }
10212  }
10213  }
10214 
10215  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(closedir(dir) == -1))
10216  {
10217  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
10218  return NULL;
10219  }
10220 #endif
10221 
10222  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(write_file(out_file, value) == -1))
10223  {
10224  /* No need to re-die aggressively. */
10225  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(last_value);
10226  return NULL;
10227  }
10228 
10229  return last_value;
10230 }

10241 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void dict_destructor(struct Dict *dict)
10242 {
10243 
10244  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(dict);
10245 
10246  for (size_t i = 0; i < dict->capacity; ++i)
10247  {
10248  struct DictKeyValue *current_pair = dict->table[i];
10249  while (current_pair != NULL)
10250  {
10251  struct DictKeyValue *next_pair = current_pair->next;
10252  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(current_pair->key);
10253  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(current_pair);
10254  current_pair = next_pair;
10255  }
10256  }
10257  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(dict->table);
10258  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(dict);
10259 }
10260 
10275 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC size_t dict_hash(const char *key, size_t capacity)
10276 {
10277  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(key);
10278 
10279  size_t hash = 5381; // Initial hash value
10280  int c; // Variable to store the current character
10281 
10282  while ((c = *key++))
10283  {
10284  hash = ((hash << 5) + hash) + c; /* hash * 33 + c */
10285  }
10286 
10287  return hash % capacity;
10288 }
10289 
10307 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int dict_reserve_more(struct Dict *dict, size_t number_of_new_elements_max_one_is_expecting)
10308 {
10309  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(dict);
10310 
10311  const size_t new_capacity = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_2(dict->capacity, number_of_new_elements_max_one_is_expecting);
10312 
10313  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_capacity == 0))
10314  {
10315  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
10316  return -1;
10317  }
10318 
10319  /* Either calloc or realloc would be ideal here, but, if the block is large,
10320  then calloc might be better because there might be a cleared block of
10321  memory that is very large that is readily available. */
10322  struct DictKeyValue **new_table = (struct DictKeyValue **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_CALLOC(new_capacity, sizeof(struct DictKeyValue *));
10323  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_table == NULL))
10324  {
10325  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
10326  return -1;
10327  }
10328 
10329  for (size_t i = 0; i < dict->capacity; ++i)
10330  {
10331  struct DictKeyValue *current_pair = dict->table[i];
10332  while (current_pair)
10333  {
10334  struct DictKeyValue *next_pair = current_pair->next;
10335  const size_t new_index = dict_hash(current_pair->key, new_capacity);
10336  current_pair->next = new_table[new_index];
10337  new_table[new_index] = current_pair;
10338  current_pair = next_pair;
10339  }
10340  }
10341 
10342  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(dict->table);
10343  dict->table = new_table;
10344  dict->capacity = new_capacity;
10345 
10346  return 0;
10347 }
10361 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int dict_resize(struct Dict *dict)
10362 {
10363 
10364  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(dict);
10365 
10366  const size_t new_capacity = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_REALLOC_REALLOCATION_ALGORITHM(dict->capacity);
10367  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_capacity == 0)) // Overflow.
10368  {
10369  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
10370  return -1;
10371  }
10372 
10373  /* Either calloc or realloc would be ideal here, but, if the block is large,
10374  then calloc might be better because there might be a cleared block of
10375  memory that is very large that is readily available. */
10376  struct DictKeyValue **new_table = (struct DictKeyValue **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_CALLOC(new_capacity, sizeof(struct DictKeyValue *));
10377  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_table == NULL))
10378  {
10379  dict_destructor(dict);
10380  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
10381  return -1;
10382  }
10383 
10384  for (size_t i = 0; i < dict->capacity; ++i)
10385  {
10386  struct DictKeyValue *current_pair = dict->table[i];
10387  while (current_pair)
10388  {
10389  struct DictKeyValue *next_pair = current_pair->next;
10390  const size_t new_index = dict_hash(current_pair->key, new_capacity);
10391  current_pair->next = new_table[new_index];
10392  new_table[new_index] = current_pair;
10393  current_pair = next_pair;
10394  }
10395  }
10396 
10397  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(dict->table);
10398  dict->table = new_table;
10399  dict->capacity = new_capacity;
10400 
10401  return 0;
10402 }
10403 
10415 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void dict_del_key(struct Dict *dict, const char *key)
10416 {
10417  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(dict);
10418  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(key);
10419  const size_t index = dict_hash(key, dict->capacity);
10420 
10421  struct DictKeyValue *current = dict->table[index];
10422  struct DictKeyValue *prev = NULL;
10423 
10424  while (current != NULL)
10425  {
10426  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRCMP(current->key, key) == 0)
10427  {
10428  /* Key found, remove the entry */
10429  if (prev == NULL)
10430  {
10431  /* If it's the first node in the linked list */
10432  dict->table[index] = current->next;
10433  }
10434  else
10435  {
10436  prev->next = current->next;
10437  }
10438 
10439  /* Free memory */
10440  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(current->key);
10441  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(current);
10442 
10443  /* Update size */
10444  --dict->size;
10445 
10446  return;
10447  }
10448 
10449  /* Move to the next node in the linked list */
10450  prev = current;
10451  current = current->next;
10452  }
10453 }
10454 
10467 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int dict_add(struct Dict *dict, const char *key, void *value)
10468 {
10469 
10470  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(dict);
10471  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(key);
10472  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(value);
10473  if ((double)dict->size / dict->capacity > FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_HASH_LOAD_FACTOR_THRESHOLD)
10474  {
10475  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(dict_resize(dict) == -1))
10476  {
10477  // Don't need to re die aggressively if enabled here because dict resize
10478  // does it.
10479  return -1;
10480  }
10481  }
10482 
10483  const size_t index = dict_hash(key, dict->capacity);
10484 
10485  struct DictKeyValue *new_pair = (struct DictKeyValue *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(sizeof(struct DictKeyValue));
10486  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_pair == NULL))
10487  {
10488  /* Keep the old key if there was one. */
10489  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
10490  return -1;
10491  }
10492 
10493  new_pair->key = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_STRDUP(key);
10494  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_pair->key == NULL))
10495  {
10496  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(new_pair);
10497  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
10498  return -1;
10499  }
10500  new_pair->next = dict->table[index];
10501  new_pair->value = value;
10502 
10503  /* If there is a hash collision */
10504  if (dict->table[index] != NULL)
10505  {
10506  struct DictKeyValue *current = new_pair->next; // First one
10507  struct DictKeyValue *prev = new_pair; // New one
10508  /* Traverse the linked list to check for duplicates */
10509  do
10510  {
10511  /* This should only ever happen once unless the dict is corrupt, so we return. */
10512  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRCMP(current->key, key) == 0)
10513  {
10514  prev->next = current->next;
10515  /* Duplicate key found */
10516  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(current->key);
10517  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(current);
10518  /* Dont increment size */
10519  /* Assume the list only has 1 key with the value (it should unless
10520  * something is really wrong). */
10521  goto end;
10522  }
10523 
10524  prev = current;
10525  current = current->next;
10526  } while (current != NULL);
10527  }
10528  ++dict->size;
10529 
10530 end:
10531  dict->table[index] = new_pair;
10532  return 0;
10533 }
10534 
10551 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void *dict_get(struct Dict *dict, const char *key)
10552 {
10553  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(dict);
10554  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(key);
10555  const size_t index = dict_hash(key, dict->capacity);
10556  struct DictKeyValue *current_pair = dict->table[index];
10557 
10558  while (current_pair != NULL)
10559  {
10560  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRCMP(current_pair->key, key) == 0)
10561  {
10562  return current_pair->value;
10563  }
10564 
10565  // Hash collision, continue with linked list.
10566  current_pair = current_pair->next;
10567  }
10568 
10569  return NULL;
10570 }

10590 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void *dict_get_check(struct Dict *dict, const char *key, int *key_is_in_dict)
10591 {
10592  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(dict);
10593  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(key);
10594  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(key_is_in_dict);

10599  while (current_pair != NULL)

10605  }

10643 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC struct FrozenDict *frozen_dict_new_instance(size_t num_pairs, ...)
10644 {
10645  struct FrozenDict *frozen_dict = (struct FrozenDict *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(sizeof(struct FrozenDict));
10646  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(frozen_dict == NULL))
10647  {
10648  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
10649  return NULL;
10650  }
10651 
10652  frozen_dict->capacity = num_pairs * FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FROZEN_INITIALIZATION_SIZE_MULTIPLIER;
10653  frozen_dict->size = 0;
10654  frozen_dict->table = (struct DictKeyValue **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_CALLOC(FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_HASH_INITIAL_CAPACITY, sizeof(struct DictKeyValue *));
10655  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(frozen_dict->table == NULL))
10656  {
10657  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(frozen_dict);
10658  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
10659  return NULL;
10660  }
10661 
10662  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_VA_LIST args;
10663  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_VA_START(args, num_pairs);
10664 
10665  for (size_t i = 0; i < num_pairs; ++i)
10666  {
10667  char *key;
10668  void *value;
10669 
10670  key = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_VA_ARG(args, char *);
10671  value = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_VA_ARG(args, void *);
10672 
10673  dict_add((struct Dict *)frozen_dict, key, value);
10674  }
10675 
10676  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_VA_END(args); // Clean up the va_list
10677 
10678  return frozen_dict;
10679 }

10767 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void dict_iter(struct Dict *dict, void (*callback)(char *key, void *value))
10768 {
10769  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(dict);
10770  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(callback);
10771 
10772  for (size_t i = 0; i < dict->capacity; ++i)
10773  {
10774  struct DictKeyValue *current = dict->table[i];
10775 
10776  while (current != NULL)
10777  {
10778  /* Call the callback function with the key and value */
10779  callback(current->key, current->value);
10780 
10781  /* Move to the next node in the linked list */
10782  current = current->next;
10783  }
10784  }
10785 }

10874 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int dict_to_array(struct Dict *dict, char ***keys, void ***values, size_t *size_of_keys_and_values)
10875 {
10876  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(dict);
10877  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(keys);
10878  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(values);
10879  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(size_of_keys_and_values);
10880 
10881  const size_t alloc_size1 = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(dict->size, sizeof(char *));
10882  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(alloc_size1 == 0))
10883  goto overflow;
10884  size_t alloc_size2;
10885 
10886  alloc_size2 = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(dict->size, sizeof(void *));
10887  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(alloc_size2 == 0))
10888  goto overflow;
10889 
10890  *keys = (char **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(alloc_size1);
10891  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(*keys == NULL))
10892  goto error_handler;
10893 
10894  *values = (void **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(alloc_size2);
10895 
10896  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(*values == NULL))
10897  {
10898  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(*keys);
10899  *keys = NULL;
10900  // Values is already NULL here.
10901  goto error_handler;
10902  }
10903 
10904  for (size_t i = 0, index = 0; i < dict->capacity; ++i)
10905  {
10906  struct DictKeyValue *current_pair = dict->table[i];
10907  while (current_pair != NULL)
10908  {
10909  (*keys)[index] = (current_pair->key);
10910  (*values)[index] = current_pair->value;
10911 
10912  ++index;
10913  current_pair = current_pair->next;
10914  }
10915  }
10916 
10917  *size_of_keys_and_values = dict->size;
10918 
10919  return 0;
10920 
10921 overflow:
10922 error_handler:
10923 
10924  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
10925  return -1;
10926 }
10927

11056 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *dict_to_string(struct Dict *dict, int pointer_or_string) /* 0 = pointer, 1 = string */
11057 {
11058  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(dict);
11059  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(pointer_or_string == 0 || pointer_or_string == 1);
11060 
11061  /* Allocate memory for the string representation */
11062  size_t total_length = 2;
11063  for (size_t i = 0; i < dict->capacity; ++i)
11064  {
11065  struct DictKeyValue *current_pair = dict->table[i];
11066  while (current_pair != NULL)
11067  {
11068  /* Calculate the length of the string representation for each key-value
11069  * pair */
11070  total_length += FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(current_pair->key) + 2; // 2 for ": "
11071  if (pointer_or_string == 0)
11072  {
11073  total_length += FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_SNPRINTF(NULL, 0, "%p",
11074  current_pair->value); // Calculate the length of the value string
11075  }
11076  else
11077  {
11078  total_length += FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_SNPRINTF(NULL, 0, "%s",
11079  (char *)current_pair->value); // Calculate the length of the value string
11080  }
11081  total_length += 2; // 2 for ", "
11082  current_pair = current_pair->next;
11083  }
11084  }
11085 
11086  // Should not reach SIZE_MAX
11087 
11088  // Add 1 for the null-terminator, at least 3 chars additional
11089  char *result = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(total_length + sizeof("")); /* Should be Safe. */
11090  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result == NULL))
11091  {
11092  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
11093  return NULL;
11094  }
11095 
11096  result[0] = '{';
11097  size_t index = 1;
11098 
11099  for (size_t i = 0; i < dict->capacity; ++i)
11100  {
11101  struct DictKeyValue *current_pair = dict->table[i];
11102  while (current_pair != NULL)
11103  {
11104  /* Append the key and value to the string representation */
11105  if (pointer_or_string == 0)
11106  {
11107  index += FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_SNPRINTF(result + index, total_length - index, "%s: %p", current_pair->key, current_pair->value);
11108  }
11109  else if (pointer_or_string == 1)
11110  {
11111  index += FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_SNPRINTF(result + index, total_length - index, "%s: %s", current_pair->key, (char *)current_pair->value);
11112  }
11113  current_pair = current_pair->next;
11114 
11115  /* Add a separator (comma) if there are more elements */
11116  if (index < total_length - 2)
11117  {
11118  result[index++] = ',';
11119  result[index++] = ' ';
11120  }
11121  }
11122  }
11123 
11124  if (dict->capacity)
11125  {
11126  index -= 2;
11127  }
11128 
11129  result[index++] = '}';
11130  result[index++] = '\0'; // Null-terminate the string
11131  return result;
11132 }
11133

11266 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void set_destructor(struct Set *set)
11267 {
11268  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(set);
11269 
11270  for (size_t i = 0; i < set->capacity; ++i)
11271  {
11272  struct SetKey *current_key = set->table[i];
11273  while (current_key != NULL)
11274  {
11275  struct SetKey *next_key = current_key->next;
11276  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(current_key->key);
11277  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(current_key);
11278  current_key = next_key;
11279  }
11280  }
11281  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(set->table);
11282  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(set);
11283 }

11292 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC struct Set *set_new_instance(void)
11293 {
11294  struct Set *set = (struct Set *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(sizeof(struct Set));
11295  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(set == NULL))
11296  {
11297  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
11298  return NULL;
11299  }
11300 
11301  set->capacity = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_HASH_INITIAL_CAPACITY;
11302  set->size = 0;
11303  set->table = (struct SetKey **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_CALLOC(FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_HASH_INITIAL_CAPACITY, sizeof(struct SetKey *));
11304  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(set->table == NULL))
11305  {
11306  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(set);
11307  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
11308  return NULL;
11309  }
11310 
11311  return set;
11312 }
11313 
11328 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC size_t set_hash(const char *key, size_t capacity)
11329 {
11330  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(key);
11331  size_t hash = 5381; // Initial hash value
11332  int c; // Variable to store the current character
11333 
11334  while ((c = *key++))
11335  {
11336  hash = ((hash << 5) + hash) + c; /* hash * 33 + c */
11337  }
11338 
11339  return hash % capacity;
11340 }
11341 
11350 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int set_resize(struct Set *set)
11351 {
11352  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(set);
11353 
11354  const size_t new_capacity = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_REALLOC_REALLOCATION_ALGORITHM(set->capacity);
11355  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_capacity == 0)) // Overflow.
11356  {
11357  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
11358  return -1;
11359  }
11360  /* Either calloc or realloc would be ideal here, but, if the block is large,
11361  then calloc might be better because there might be a cleared block of
11362  memory that is very large that is readily available. */
11363  struct SetKey **new_table = (struct SetKey **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_CALLOC(new_capacity, sizeof(struct SetKey *));
11364  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_table == NULL))
11365  {
11366  set_destructor(set);
11367  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
11368  return -1;
11369  }
11370 
11371  for (size_t i = 0; i < set->capacity; ++i)
11372  {
11373  struct SetKey *current_key = set->table[i];
11374  while (current_key)
11375  {
11376  struct SetKey *next_key = current_key->next;
11377  const size_t new_index = set_hash(current_key->key, new_capacity);
11378  current_key->next = new_table[new_index];
11379  new_table[new_index] = current_key;
11380  current_key = next_key;
11381  }
11382  }
11383 
11384  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(set->table);
11385  set->table = new_table;
11386  set->capacity = new_capacity;
11387 
11388  return 0;
11389 }
11390 
11399 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC void set_del_key(struct Set *set, const char *key)
11400 {
11401  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(set);
11402  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(key);
11403 
11404  const size_t index = set_hash(key, set->capacity);
11405 
11406  struct SetKey *current = set->table[index];
11407  struct SetKey *prev = NULL;
11408 
11409  while (current != NULL)
11410  {
11411  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRCMP(current->key, key) == 0)
11412  {
11413  /* Key found, remove the entry */
11414  if (prev == NULL)
11415  {
11416  /* If it's the first node in the linked list */
11417  set->table[index] = current->next;
11418  }
11419  else
11420  {
11421  prev->next = current->next;
11422  }
11423 
11424  /* Free memory */
11425  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(current->key);
11426  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(current);
11427 
11428  /* Update size */
11429  --set->size;
11430 
11431  return;
11432  }
11433 
11434  /* Move to the next node in the linked list */
11435  prev = current;
11436  current = current->next;
11437  }
11438 }
11439 
11451 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int set_add(struct Set *set, const char *key)
11452 {
11453  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(set);
11454  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(key);
11455 
11456  if ((double)set->size / set->capacity > FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_HASH_LOAD_FACTOR_THRESHOLD)
11457  {
11458  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(set_resize(set) == -1))
11459  {
11460  // Don't need to re die aggressively if enabled here because set resize does it.
11461  return -1;
11462  }
11463  }
11464 
11465  const size_t index = set_hash(key, set->capacity);
11466 
11467  struct SetKey *new_set_key = (struct SetKey *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(sizeof(struct SetKey));
11468  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_set_key == NULL))
11469  {
11470  /* Keep the old key if there was one. */
11471  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
11472  return -1;
11473  }
11474 
11475  new_set_key->key = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_STRDUP(key);
11476  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_set_key->key == NULL))
11477  {
11478  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(new_set_key);
11479  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
11480  return -1;
11481  }
11482  new_set_key->next = set->table[index];
11483 
11484  /* If there is a hash collision */
11485  if (set->table[index] != NULL)
11486  {
11487  struct SetKey *current = new_set_key->next; // First one
11488  struct SetKey *prev = new_set_key; // New one
11489  /* Traverse the linked list to check for duplicates */
11490  do
11491  {
11492  /* This should only ever happen once unless the set is corrupt, so we return. */
11493 
11494  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRCMP(current->key, key) == 0)
11495  { /* Duplicate key found */
11496  prev->next = current->next;
11497 
11498  // Free the old key
11499  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(current->key);
11500  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(current);
11501 
11502  /* Dont increment size */
11503  /* Assume the list only has 1 key with the value (it should unless
11504  * something is really wrong). */
11505 
11506  goto end;
11507  }
11508 
11509  prev = current;
11510  current = current->next;
11511  } while (current != NULL);
11512  }
11513 
11514  ++set->size;
11515 end:
11516  set->table[index] = new_set_key;
11517  return 0;
11518 }
11519 
11536 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int set_reserve_more(struct Set *set, size_t number_of_new_elements_max_one_is_expecting)
11537 {
11538  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(set);
11539 
11540  const size_t new_capacity = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_2(set->capacity, number_of_new_elements_max_one_is_expecting);
11541  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_capacity == 0)) // Overflow.
11542  {
11543  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
11544  return -1;
11545  }
11546  /* Either calloc or realloc would be ideal here, but, if the block is large,
11547  then calloc might be better because there might be a cleared block of
11548  memory that is very large that is readily available. */
11549  struct SetKey **new_table = (struct SetKey **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_CALLOC(new_capacity, sizeof(struct SetKey *));
11550  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_table == NULL))
11551  {
11552  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
11553  return -1;
11554  }
11555 
11556  for (size_t i = 0; i < set->capacity; ++i)
11557  {
11558  struct SetKey *current_key = set->table[i];
11559  while (current_key)
11560  {
11561  struct SetKey *next_key = current_key->next;
11562  const size_t new_index = set_hash(current_key->key, new_capacity);
11563  current_key->next = new_table[new_index];
11564  new_table[new_index] = current_key;
11565  current_key = next_key;
11566  }
11567  }
11568 
11569  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(set->table);
11570  set->table = new_table;
11571  set->capacity = new_capacity;
11572 
11573  return 0;
11574 }

11585 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int set_in(struct Set *set, const char *key)
11586 {
11587  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(set);
11588  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(key);
11589 
11590  const size_t index = set_hash(key, set->capacity);
11591  struct SetKey *current_key = set->table[index];
11592 
11593  while (current_key != NULL)
11594  {
11595  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRCMP(current_key->key, key) == 0)
11596  {
11597  return 1;
11598  }
11599  current_key = current_key->next;
11600  }
11601 
11602  return 0;
11603 }

11628 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC struct FrozenSet *frozen_set_new_instance(size_t num_args, ...)
11629 {
11630  struct FrozenSet *frozen_set = (struct FrozenSet *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(sizeof(struct FrozenSet));
11631  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(frozen_set == NULL))
11632  {
11633  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
11634  return NULL;
11635  }
11636 
11637  frozen_set->capacity = num_args * FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FROZEN_INITIALIZATION_SIZE_MULTIPLIER;
11638  frozen_set->size = 0;
11639  frozen_set->table = (struct SetKey **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_CALLOC(FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_HASH_INITIAL_CAPACITY, sizeof(struct SetKey *));
11640  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(frozen_set->table == NULL))
11641  {
11642  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(frozen_set);
11643  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
11644  return NULL;
11645  }
11646 
11647  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_VA_LIST args;
11648  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_VA_START(args, num_args);
11649 
11650  for (size_t i = 0; i < num_args; ++i)
11651  {
11652  char *key;
11653 
11654  key = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_VA_ARG(args, char *);
11655  set_add((struct Set *)frozen_set, key);
11656  }
11657 
11658  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_VA_END(args); // Clean up the va_list
11659 
11660  return frozen_set;
11661 }

11758 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int set_to_array(struct Set *set, char ***keys, size_t *size_of_keys)
11759 {
11760  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(set);
11761  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(keys);
11762 
11763  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(size_of_keys);
11764 
11765  const size_t alloc_size1 = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_mul(set->size, sizeof(char *));
11766  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(alloc_size1 == 0))
11767  goto overflow;
11768 
11769  *keys = (char **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(alloc_size1);
11770  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(*keys == NULL))
11771  goto error_handler;
11772 
11773  for (size_t i = 0, index = 0; i < set->capacity; ++i)
11774  {
11775  struct SetKey *current_pair = set->table[i];
11776  while (current_pair != NULL)
11777  {
11778  (*keys)[index] = (current_pair->key);
11779 
11780  ++index;
11781  current_pair = current_pair->next;
11782  }
11783  }
11784 
11785  *size_of_keys = set->size;
11786 
11787  return 0;
11788 
11789 overflow:
11790 error_handler:
11791 
11792  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
11793  return -1;
11794 }

11855 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *set_to_string(struct Set *set)
11856 {
11857 
11858  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(set);
11859 
11860  /* Allocate memory for the string representation */
11861  size_t total_length = 2;
11862  for (size_t i = 0; i < set->capacity; ++i)
11863  {
11864  struct SetKey *current_key = set->table[i];
11865  while (current_key != NULL)
11866  {
11867  /* Calculate the length of the string representation for each key-value
11868  * pair */
11869  total_length += FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRLEN(current_key->key);
11870  total_length += 2; // 2 for ", "
11871  current_key = current_key->next;
11872  }
11873  }
11874 
11875  // Should not reach SIZE_MAX
11876 
11877  // Add 1 for the null-terminator, at least 3 chars additional
11878 
11879  char *result = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(total_length + sizeof("")); /* Safe */
11880 
11881  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result == NULL))
11882  {
11883  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
11884  return NULL;
11885  }
11886 
11887  result[0] = '{';
11888  size_t index = 1;
11889 
11890  for (size_t i = 0; i < set->capacity; ++i)
11891  {
11892  struct SetKey *current_key = set->table[i];
11893  while (current_key != NULL)
11894  {
11895  /* Append the key and value to the string representation */
11896  index += FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_SNPRINTF(result + index, total_length - index, "%s", current_key->key);
11897  current_key = current_key->next;
11898 
11899  /* Add a separator (comma) if there are more elements */
11900  if (index < total_length - 2)
11901  {
11902  result[index++] = ',';
11903  result[index++] = ' ';
11904  }
11905  }
11906  }
11907 
11908  if (set->capacity)
11909  {
11910  index -= 2;
11911  }
11912  result[index++] = '}';
11913  result[index++] = '\0'; // Null-terminate the string
11914  return result;
11915 }
11916 
11930 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *frozen_set_to_string(struct FrozenSet *frozen_set)
11931 {
11932  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(frozen_set);
11933 
11934  /* Allocate memory for the string representation */

11939  while (current_key != NULL)

11953  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(result == NULL))

11989 }

12042 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int is_valid_utf8(const char *str, size_t len)
12043 {
12044  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(str);
12045 
12046  size_t i = 0;
12047 
12048  while (i < len)
12049  {
12050  if ((str[i] & 0x80) == 0)
12051  {
12052  // ASCII character (0xxxxxxx)
12053  ++i;
12054  }
12055  else if ((str[i] & 0xE0) == 0xC0)
12056  {
12057  // 2-byte UTF-8 character (110xxxxx)
12058  if (i + 1 >= len || (str[i + 1] & 0xC0) != 0x80)
12059  return 0;
12060  i += 2;
12061  }
12062  else if ((str[i] & 0xF0) == 0xE0)
12063  {
12064  // 3-byte UTF-8 character (1110xxxx)
12065  if (i + 2 >= len || (str[i + 1] & 0xC0) != 0x80 || (str[i + 2] & 0xC0) != 0x80)
12066  return 0;
12067  i += 3;
12068  }
12069  else if ((str[i] & 0xF8) == 0xF0)
12070  {
12071  // 4-byte UTF-8 character (11110xxx)
12072  if (i + 3 >= len || (str[i + 1] & 0xC0) != 0x80 || (str[i + 2] & 0xC0) != 0x80 || (str[i + 3] & 0xC0) != 0x80)
12073  return 0;
12074  i += 4;
12075  }
12076  else
12077  {
12078  // Invalid UTF-8 encoding
12079  return 0;
12080  }
12081  }
12082 
12083  return 1;
12084 }
12085 
12095 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC const char *sample_strings(const char **strings, size_t size) /* Does not dynamically allocate memory. */
12096 {
12097  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(strings);
12098 
12099  long j;
12100 
12101 #ifdef _WIN32
12102  unsigned int rand_val;
12103  if (rand_s(&rand_val) != 0)
12104  {
12105  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
12106  return NULL;
12107  }
12108 
12109  j = rand_val % size;
12110 #elif defined(__linux__)
12111  j = (long)(drand48() * size);
12112 #else
12113  j = rand() % size;
12114 #endif
12115 
12116  return strings[j];
12117 }
12118 
12128 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int shuffle_strings_in_place(char **strings, size_t size)
12129 {
12130  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(strings);
12131 
12132  for (size_t i = size - 1; i; --i)
12133  {
12134  long j;
12135 #ifdef _WIN32
12136  unsigned int rand_val;
12137  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(rand_s(&rand_val) != 0))
12138  {
12139  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
12140  return -1;
12141  }
12142 
12143  j = rand_val % (i + 1);
12144 #elif defined(__linux__)
12145  j = (long)(drand48() * (i + 1));
12146 #else
12147  j = rand() % (i + 1);
12148 #endif
12149 
12150  // Swap strings[i] and strings[j]
12151  char *temp = strings[i];
12152  strings[i] = strings[j];
12153  strings[j] = temp;
12154  }
12155 
12156  return 0;
12157 }

12168 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC long rand_number_from_range_inclusive_signed(signed long min, signed long max)
12169 {
12170  const signed long long range = max - min + 1;
12171 
12172 #ifdef _WIN32
12173  unsigned int rand_val;
12174  if (rand_s(&rand_val) != 0)
12175  {
12176  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
12177  return 0;
12178  }
12179 
12180  return min + (rand_val % range);
12181 #elif defined(__linux__)
12182  return min + (long)(drand48() * range);
12183 #else
12184  return min + (rand() % range);
12185 #endif
12186 }

12197 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC unsigned long rand_number_from_range_inclusive_unsigned(unsigned long min, unsigned long max)
12198 {
12199  const unsigned long range = max - min + 1;
12200 
12201 #ifdef _WIN32
12202  unsigned int rand_val;
12203  if (rand_s(&rand_val) != 0)
12204  {
12205  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
12206  return 0;
12207  }
12208 
12209  return min + (rand_val % range);
12210 #elif defined(__linux__)
12211  return min + (unsigned long)(drand48() * range);
12212 #else
12213  return min + (rand() % range);
12214 #endif
12215 }
12216 
12217 #if FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNSAFE_FUNCTIONS_ENABLED
12238 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char *backticks(const char *command, size_t *size)
12239 {
12240  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(command);
12241  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(size);
12242 
12243  FILE *pipe = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_POPEN(command, "r");
12244  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(pipe == NULL))
12245  {
12246  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
12247  return NULL; // Indicate error by returning NULL
12248  }
12249 
12250  // Read the command output into the string
12251  size_t output_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_POPEN_INITIAL_ALLOC_SIZE; // Initial output buffer size
12252  char *output = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(output_size);
12253  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(output == NULL))
12254  {
12255  pclose(pipe); // No need to check errors here because things are already
12256  // going wrong.
12257  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
12258  return NULL;
12259  }
12260 
12261  size_t total_read = 0;
12262 
12263  for (;;)
12264  {
12265  const size_t read_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FREAD(output + total_read, 1, 4096, pipe);
12266 
12267  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(read_size == 0))
12268  {
12269  const int error_code = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FERROR(pipe);
12270  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(error_code))
12271  {
12272  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(output);
12273  pclose(pipe); // No need to check errors here because things are already
12274  // going wrong.
12275  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
12276  return NULL;
12277  }
12278  else
12279  {
12280  break;
12281  }
12282  }
12283  else if (total_read + read_size + 1 > output_size)
12284  {
12285  const size_t new_realloc_length = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_safe_add_3(total_read, read_size, 1);
12286 
12287  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_realloc_length == 0))
12288  {
12289  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(output);
12290  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
12291  return NULL;
12292  }
12293  // Expand the buffer
12294  output_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_REALLOC_REALLOCATION_ALGORITHM(new_realloc_length);
12295 
12296  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(output_size == 0)) // Overflow.
12297  {
12298  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
12299  return NULL;
12300  }
12301  char *new_output = (char *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_REALLOC(output, output_size);
12302 
12303  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(new_output == NULL))
12304  {
12305  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(output);
12306  pclose(pipe); // No need to check errors here because things are already
12307  // going wrong.
12308  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
12309  return NULL;
12310  }
12311 
12312  output = new_output;
12313  }
12314  total_read += read_size;
12315  }
12316 
12317  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(ferror(pipe) != 0))
12318  {
12319  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(output);
12320 
12321  pclose(pipe); // No need to re check for errors because things are going wrong.
12322 
12323  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
12324 
12325  return NULL; // Error reading from pipe
12326  }
12327 
12328  // Null-terminate the string
12329  output[total_read] = '\0';
12330 
12331  *size = total_read;
12332 
12333  // Close the pipe
12334  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(pclose(pipe) != 0)) // Check for errors.
12335  {
12336  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE(output);
12337  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
12338  return NULL;
12339  }
12340 
12341  return output;
12342 }
12343 
12344 #endif
12345 
12366 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC char **read_file_into_array(const char *filename, const char *delim, size_t *num_lines)
12367 {
12368  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(filename);
12369  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(delim);
12370  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(num_lines);
12371 
12372  size_t size_of_file;
12373 
12374  *num_lines = 0;
12375 
12376  /*
12377  * This approach uses very few system calls and is rather efficient.
12378  * It first gets the entire file into memory, then splits it.
12379  * There would be very few fread() calls, and it can predict the buffer
12380  * size ahead of time, for low memory usage.
12381  *
12382  * One issue with this is that it has to allocate memory twice -
12383  * first for read_file_into_array - second for the new array,
12384  * after which the first array is freed(). So that means for
12385  * a time, the computer needs around 2x the memory.
12386  * However, if you are concerned about memory usage, probably
12387  * better might be read_file_into_string() with strtok() used
12388  * to extract the parts you want, or manual code withFOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FREAD().
12389  *
12390  * Any which way, this implementation is decent and efficient
12391  * for many purposes.
12392  */
12393  const char *file = read_file_into_string(filename, &size_of_file);
12394  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(file == NULL))
12395  {
12396  /* read_file_into_string() would already call die_aggressively_if_enabled */
12397 
12398  return NULL;
12399  }
12400 
12401  char **lines = split(file, num_lines, delim, 0, 1);
12402 
12403  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_FREE((void *)file);
12404  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(lines == NULL))
12405  {
12406  /* split() would already call die_aggressively_if_enabled */
12407 
12408  return NULL;
12409  }
12410 
12411  return lines;
12412 }

12698 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC size_t count_occurrences_of_string_in_array(const char **array, const char *string, size_t array_length)
12699 {
12700  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(array);
12701 
12702  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(string);
12703 
12704  size_t count = 0;
12705 
12706  // Iterate through the array
12707  for (size_t i = 0; i < array_length; ++i)
12708  {
12709  // Compare each string in the array with the target string
12710  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_STRCMP(array[i], string) == 0)
12711  {
12712  ++count;
12713  }
12714  }
12715 
12716  return count;
12717 }

12732 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC size_t count_occurrences_of_adjacent_data_in_array(const void *array_of_adjacent_values, size_t array_length, const void *memory, size_t memory_length)
12733 {
12734

12794 /* Write callback */
12795 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC size_t FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_libcurl_write_callback(char *data, size_t n, size_t l, void *userp)
12796 {
12797 
12798  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(data);
12799 
12800  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(userp);
12801  struct StringData
12802  {
12803  char *string;
12804 
12805  size_t size;
12806  size_t alloc_size;
12807 
12808  size_t byte_max_cutoff;
12809  } *string = userp;
12810 
12811  const size_t both = n * l;
12812  append_string_to_string(&string->string, &string->size, &string->alloc_size, data, both);
12813 
12814  if (string->byte_max_cutoff != 0 && string->size >= string->byte_max_cutoff)
12815  {
12816  /* Curl can read in big blocks, like 9,370 bytes. So if the cutoff is low,
12817  * the read size still might be high. */
12818  /* FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_PRINTF("%zu.size >= %zu.byte_max_cutoff\n", string->size,
12819  string->byte_max_cutoff); */
12820  return CURLE_OK;
12821  }
12822  return both;
12823 }

12862 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int download_website(const char *website, char **string, size_t *size, size_t *str_alloc_size, size_t byte_max_cutoff, const char *user_agent)
12863 {
12864 
12865  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(website);
12866  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(string);
12867  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(size);
12868  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(str_alloc_size);
12869 
12870  CURL *curl = curl_easy_init();
12871  if (FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_UNLIKELY(curl == NULL))
12872  {
12873  return -1;
12874  }
12875 
12876  if (user_agent == NULL)
12877  {
12878  user_agent = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_DEFAULT_USER_AGENT;
12879  }
12880 
12881  curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_BUFFERSIZE, 102400L);
12882  curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_URL, website);
12883  curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_NOPROGRESS, 1L);
12884  curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_USERAGENT, user_agent);
12885  curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_FOLLOWLOCATION, 1L);
12886  curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_MAXREDIRS, 50L);
12887  curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_HTTP_VERSION, (long)CURL_HTTP_VERSION_2TLS);
12888  curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_FTP_SKIP_PASV_IP, 1L);
12889  curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_TCP_KEEPALIVE, 1L);
12890  struct StringData
12891  {
12892  char *string;
12893  size_t size;
12894  size_t alloc_size;
12895  size_t byte_max_cutoff;
12896  } data;
12897  data.string = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_MALLOC(FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_INITIAL_NETWORK_DOWNLOAD_BUFFER_SIZE);
12898  data.alloc_size = FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_INITIAL_NETWORK_DOWNLOAD_BUFFER_SIZE;
12899  data.size = 0;
12900  data.byte_max_cutoff = byte_max_cutoff;
12901 
12902  curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_WRITEFUNCTION, FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_libcurl_write_callback);
12903  curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_WRITEDATA, &data);
12904  CURLcode curlcode = curl_easy_perform(curl);
12905 
12906  curl_easy_cleanup(curl);
12907 
12908  *string = data.string;
12909  *size = data.size;
12910  *str_alloc_size = data.alloc_size;
12911 
12912  return curlcode == CURLE_OK;
12913 }

12935 FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_FUNC int download_websites(const char **websites_to_download, size_t num_websites, char ***outputs, size_t **lens, size_t byte_limit, int aggressive_stop_on_error)
12936 {
12937 
12938  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(websites_to_download);
12939  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(outputs);
12940  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_ASSERT_ARGUMENT_IF_ENABLED(lens);
12941  // Initalize all to NULL in case a site can't download
12942  *outputs = (char **)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_CALLOC(num_websites, sizeof(char *));
12943 
12944  // Initalize all to 0 in case a site can't download
12945  *lens = (size_t *)FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_MEMORY_ALLOCATOR_CALLOC(num_websites, sizeof(size_t));
12946 
12947  for (size_t i = 0; i < num_websites; ++i)
12948  {
12949  size_t alloc_size;
12950  if (download_website(websites_to_download[i], (*outputs) + i, (*lens) + i, &alloc_size, byte_limit, NULL) == -1)
12951  {
12952  if (aggressive_stop_on_error)
12953  {
12954  FOUNDATIONAL_LIB_die_aggressively_if_enabled();
12955  return -1;
12956  }
12957  }
12958  }
12959 
12960  return 0;
12961 }
